Entities.Name: UnitSymbol
Entities.Description:
The derived units defined for usage in the CIM. In some cases, the derived unit is equal to an SI unit. Whenever possible, the standard derived symbol is used instead of the formula for the derived unit. For example, the unit symbol Farad is defined as "F" instead of "CPerV". In cases where a standard symbol does not exist for a derived unit, the formula for the unit is used as the unit symbol. For example, density does not have a standard symbol and so it is represented as "kgPerm3". With the exception of the "kg", which is an SI unit, the unit symbols do not contain multipliers and therefore represent the base derived unit to which a multiplier can be applied as a whole. 
Every unit symbol is treated as an unparseable text as if it were a single-letter symbol. The meaning of each unit symbol is defined by the accompanying descriptive text and not by the text contents of the unit symbol.
To allow the widest possible range of serializations without requiring special character handling, several substitutions are made which deviate from the format described in IEC 80000-1. The division symbol "/" is replaced by the letters "Per". Exponents are written in plain text after the unit as "m3" instead of being formatted as "m" with a superscript of 3  or introducing a symbol as in "m^3". The degree symbol "°" is replaced with the letters "deg". Any clarification of the meaning for a substitution is included in the description for the unit symbol.
Non-SI units are included in list of unit symbols to allow sources of data to be correctly labelled with their non-SI units (for example, a GPS sensor that is reporting numbers that represent feet instead of meters). This allows software to use the unit symbol information correctly convert and scale the raw data of those sources into SI-based units. 
The integer values are used for harmonization with IEC 61850.

Entities.Name: UnitMultiplier
Entities.Description:
The unit multipliers defined for the CIM.  When applied to unit symbols, the unit symbol is treated as a derived unit. Regardless of the contents of the unit symbol text, the unit symbol shall be treated as if it were a single-character unit symbol. Unit symbols should not contain multipliers, and it should be left to the multiplier to define the multiple for an entire data type. 

For example, if a unit symbol is "m2Pers" and the multiplier is "k", then the value is k(m**2/s), and the multiplier applies to the entire final value, not to any individual part of the value. This can be conceptualized by substituting a derived unit symbol for the unit type. If one imagines that the symbol "Þ" represents the derived unit "m2Pers", then applying the multiplier "k" can be conceptualized simply as "kÞ".

For example, the SI unit for mass is "kg" and not "g".  If the unit symbol is defined as "kg", then the multiplier is applied to "kg" as a whole and does not replace the "k" in front of the "g". In this case, the multiplier of "m" would be used with the unit symbol of "kg" to represent one gram.  As a text string, this violates the instructions in IEC 80000-1. However, because the unit symbol in CIM is treated as a derived unit instead of as an SI unit, it makes more sense to conceptualize the "kg" as if it were replaced by one of the proposed replacements for the SI mass symbol. If one imagines that the "kg" were replaced by a symbol "Þ", then it is easier to conceptualize the multiplier "m" as creating the proper unit "mÞ", and not the forbidden unit "mkg".

Entities.Name: Impedance
Entities.Description: Ratio of voltage to current.

Entities.Name: Date
Entities.Description: Date as "yyyy-mm-dd", which conforms with ISO 8601. UTC time zone is specified as "yyyy-mm-ddZ". A local timezone relative UTC is specified as "yyyy-mm-dd(+/-)hh:mm".

Entities.Name: Pressure
Entities.Description: Pressure in pascals.

Entities.Name: Emission
Entities.Description: Quantity of emission per fuel heat content.

Entities.Name: VoltagePerReactivePower
Entities.Description: Voltage variation with reactive power.

Entities.Name: CapacitancePerLength
Entities.Description: Capacitance per unit of length.

Entities.Name: ActivePowerChangeRate
Entities.Description: Rate of change of active power per time.

Entities.Name: ReactancePerLength
Entities.Description: Reactance (imaginary part of impedance) per unit of length, at rated frequency.

Entities.Name: Card
Entities.Description: Documentation of the tender when it is a type of card (credit, debit, etc).

Attributes.Name: accountHolderName
Attributes.Description: Name of account holder.

Attributes.Name: expiryDate
Attributes.Description: The date when this card expires.

Attributes.Name: cvNumber
Attributes.Description: The card verification number.

Attributes.Name: pan
Attributes.Description: The primary account number.

Entities.Name: Due
Entities.Description: Details on amounts due for an account.

Attributes.Name: arrears
Attributes.Description: Part of 'current' that constitutes the arrears portion.

Attributes.Name: current
Attributes.Description: Current total amount now due: current = principle + arrears + interest + charges. Typically the rule for settlement priority is: interest dues, then arrears dues, then current dues, then charge dues.

Attributes.Name: principle
Attributes.Description: Part of 'current' that constitutes the portion of the principle amount currently due.

Attributes.Name: charges
Attributes.Description: Part of 'current' that constitutes the charge portion: 'charges' = 'Charge.fixedPortion' + 'Charge.variablePortion'.

Attributes.Name: interest
Attributes.Description: Part of 'current' that constitutes the interest portion.

Entities.Name: LineDetail
Entities.Description: Details on an amount line, with rounding, date and note.

Attributes.Name: amount
Attributes.Description: Amount for this line item.

Attributes.Name: note
Attributes.Description: Free format note relevant to this line.

Attributes.Name: dateTime
Attributes.Description: Date and time when this line was created in the application process.

Attributes.Name: rounding
Attributes.Description: Totalised monetary value of all errors due to process rounding or truncating that is not reflected in 'amount'.

Entities.Description: Unit for accounting; use either 'energyUnit' or 'currencyUnit' to specify the unit for 'value'.

Attributes.Description: Unit of service.

Attributes.Name: monetaryUnit
Attributes.Description: Unit of currency.

Attributes.Name: multiplier
Attributes.Description: Multiplier for the 'energyUnit' or 'monetaryUnit'.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: Value expressed in applicable units.

Attributes.Description: Entity that delivers the service to the customer.

Attributes.Name: other
Attributes.Description: Other kind of supplier.

Entities.Description: Details of a bank account.

Attributes.Description: Operational account reference number.

Attributes.Name: branchCode
Attributes.Description: Branch of bank where account is held.

Attributes.Name: holderName
Attributes.Description: Name of account holder.

Attributes.Name: bankName
Attributes.Description: Name of bank where account is held.

Attributes.Name: holderID
Attributes.Description: National identity number (or equivalent) of account holder.

Entities.Name: TimeTariffInterval
Entities.Description: One of a sequence of time intervals defined in terms of real time. It is typically used in association with TariffProfile to define the intervals in a time of use tariff structure, where startDateTime simultaneously determines the starting point of this interval and the ending point of the previous interval.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: A sequential reference that defines the identity of this interval and its relative position with respect to other intervals in a sequence of intervals.

Attributes.Name: startTime
Attributes.Description: A real time marker that defines the starting time (typically it is the time of day) for this interval. The interval extends to the start of the next interval or until it is reset to the start of the first interval by TariffProfile.tariffCycle.

Entities.Name: ChargeKind
Entities.Description: Kind of charge.

Attributes.Name: consumptionCharge
Attributes.Description: The charge levied for the actual usage of the service, normally expressed in terms of a tariff. For example: usage x price per kWh = total charge for consumption.

Attributes.Name: demandCharge
Attributes.Description: The charge related to the usage within a defined time interval, normally expressed in terms of a tariff. For example: a maximum-demand tariff will levy an additional charge on top of the consumption charge if the usage exceeds a defined limit per hour.

Attributes.Name: auxiliaryCharge
Attributes.Description: Any other charge which is not a consumptionCharge or demandCharge. For example: debt recovery, arrears, standing charge or charge for another service such as street lighting.

Attributes.Name: taxCharge
Attributes.Description: Any charge that is classified as a tax of a kind. For example: VAT, GST, TV tax, etc.

Attributes.Name: other
Attributes.Description: Other kind of charge.

Entities.Name: ConsumptionTariffInterval
Entities.Description: One of a sequence of intervals defined in terms of consumption quantity of a service such as electricity, water, gas, etc. It is typically used in association with TariffProfile to define the steps or blocks in a step tariff structure, where startValue simultaneously defines the entry value of this step and the closing value of the previous step. Where consumption is >= startValue it falls within this interval and where consumption is < startValue it falls within the previous interval.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: A sequential reference that defines the identity of this interval and its relative position with respect to other intervals in a sequence of intervals.

Attributes.Name: startValue
Attributes.Description: The lowest level of consumption that defines the starting point of this interval. The interval extends to the start of the next interval or until it is reset to the start of the first interval by TariffProfile.tariffCycle.

Entities.Name: FScale
Entities.Description:
Fujita scale (referred to as EF-scale starting in 2007) for tornado damage.  A set of wind estimates (not measurements) based on damage. It uses three-second gusts estimated at the point of damage based on a judgment of 8 levels of damage to 28 indicators. These estimates vary with height and exposure.  
The 3 second gust is not the same wind as in standard surface observations.
Enumerations based on NOAA conventions.

Attributes.Name: two
Attributes.Description: 111-135 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Name: four
Attributes.Description: 166-200 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Name: minusNine
Attributes.Description: Unknown.

Attributes.Name: zero
Attributes.Description: 65-85 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Name: one
Attributes.Description: 86-110 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Name: three
Attributes.Description: 136-165 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Name: five
Attributes.Description: Over 200 mph 3-second gust.

Attributes.Description: The temperature measured b<font color="#0f0f0f">y a thermometer exposed to the air in a place sheltered from direct solar radiation. </font>Also known as "dry bulb" because<font color="#0f0f0f"> the air temperature is indicated by a thermometer not affecte</font>d by the moisture of the air.

Attributes.Description: The temperature of how cold it "feels like" based on the rate of heat loss from exposed skin caused by the effects of wind and cold temperatures.

Attributes.Name: windSpeedPeak
Attributes.Description:
Peak instantaneous wind speed in the 60 minutes preceding a moment in time as long as peak speed greater than 25 knots.  
0 value means speed did not exceed 25 knots during preceding 60 minutes.

Attributes.Name: windSpeedSustained
Attributes.Description: Average instantaneous wind speed over the 2-minute time period preceding a moment in time.

Attributes.Name: dewPoint
Attributes.Description: The temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure and constant water-vapor content in order for saturation to occur. In other words, it is the temperature at which water vapor starts to condense out of the air.

Attributes.Name: windSpeedGust
Attributes.Description:
Maximum instantaneous wind speed in the 10 minute period preceding a moment in time so long as more than 10 knots of difference has been exhibited between peaks and lulls during that 10 minute time period. 
0 value means no gusts during preceding 10 minute period.

Attributes.Name: windSpeedInstantaneous

Attributes.Name: carbonDioxide
Attributes.Description: CO2 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: nitrogen
Attributes.Description: N2 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: totalCombustibleGasPercent
Attributes.Description: Total Combustible Gas (TCG) measured in headspace (in percent by volume).

Attributes.Name: carbon
Attributes.Description: C? concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: carbon4
Attributes.Description: C4 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: isobutane
Attributes.Description: isoC4 (C4H10) concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre). Isobutane is also known as methylpropane.

Attributes.Name: totalDissolvedCombustibleGas
Attributes.Description: Total dissolved combustible gas concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre). Calculated by adding the ppm of combustible gasses: hydrogen (H2), methane (CH4), ethane (C2H6), ethylene (C2H4), acetylene (C2H2), and carbon monoxide (CO).

Attributes.Name: totalPartialPressure
Attributes.Description:
Total partial pressure (in Pa).
Calculated value reflecting total of partial pressures of all combustible gasses.

Attributes.Name: hydranPredicted
Attributes.Description:
Predicted hydran value (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre), calculated based on individual measured dissolved gas concentrations.
- H2: 100 % of concentration
- CO: 15 ± 4 % of concentration
- C2H2: 8 ± 2 % of concentration
- C2H4: 1.5 ± 0.5 % of concentration

Attributes.Name: methane
Attributes.Description: CH4 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: ethylene
Attributes.Description: C2H4 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: carbonMonoxide
Attributes.Description: CO concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: propene
Attributes.Description: C3H6 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: oxygen
Attributes.Description: O2 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: totalDissolvedGasPercent
Attributes.Description: Total dissolved gas in oil (in percent by volume). Derived from the total area of all the gas peaks in the chromatogram.

Attributes.Name: butane
Attributes.Description: C4H10 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: carbon3
Attributes.Description: C3 concentration (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre).

Attributes.Name: equivalentTCGPercent
Attributes.Description:
Equivalent Total Combustible Gas (ETCG) percent.
An estimate, calculated from the dissolved-gas concentrations and the oil sample temperature, of what the TCG would be in a gas space in equilibrium with the oil. ETCG reflects what the TCG would be in air spaces near the oil.

Attributes.Name: totalHeatGas
Attributes.Description: Sum of concentrations of methane, ethane, and ethylene (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre). Used in some diagnostic gas ratios, especially THG/acetylene, which compares “heat gas” to “arcing gas.”

Attributes.Name: estimatedSafeHandlingLimit
Attributes.Description:
Estimated Safe Handling Limit (ESHL) (in percent). Estimated safe handling limit is an estimate of the lower flammability limit (LFL) of the combustible gas mixture which the dissolved gas in the oil would give off by the oil if exposed to air. 
Expressed in percent like the equivalent total combustible gas percent, it is calculated from the dissolved-gas concentrations, the oil sample temperature, and the lower flammability limits of the individual combustible gases.

Attributes.Name: hydran
Attributes.Description:
Measured composite of dissolved fault gas concentrations (in ppm, specifically in microlitre/litre). Relative sensitivity
- H2: 100 % of concentration
- CO: 15 ± 4 % of concentration
- C2H2: 8 ± 2 % of concentration
- C2H4: 1.5 ± 0.5 % of concentration.

Entities.Name: StaticLoadModelKind
Entities.Description: Type of static load model.

Attributes.Name: exponential
Attributes.Description:
This model is an exponential representation of the load. Exponential equations for active and reactive power are used and the following attributes are required:
kp1, kp2, kp3, kpf, ep1, ep2, ep3
kq1, kq2, kq3, kqf, eq1, eq2, eq3.

Attributes.Name: zIP1
Attributes.Description:
This model integrates the frequency-dependent load (primarily motors).  ZIP1 equations for active and reactive power are used and the following attributes are required:
kp1, kp2, kp3, kpf
kq1, kq2, kq3, kqf.

Attributes.Name: zIP2
Attributes.Description:
This model separates the frequency-dependent load (primarily motors) from other load.  ZIP2 equations for active and reactive power are used and the following attributes are required:
kp1, kp2, kp3, kq4, kpf
kq1, kq2, kq3, kq4, kqf.

Attributes.Name: constantZ
Attributes.Description: The load is represented as a constant impedance.  ConstantZ equations are used  for active and reactive power and no attributes are required.

Entities.Name: Delay

Attributes.Name: tm
Attributes.Description: Time constant.

Entities.Name: EnvironmentalPhenomenon
Entities.Description: The actual or forecast characteristics of an environmental phenomenon at a specific point in time (or during a specific time interval) that may have both a center and area/line location.

DerivedEntities.Name: AtmosphericPhenomenon
DerivedEntities.Description: An atmospheric phenomenon with a base and altitude providing the vertical coverage (combined with the Location to provide three dimensional space).

DerivedEntities.Name: CloudCondition
DerivedEntities.Description: A classified cloud phenomenon with a type.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: The type of the cloud as defined by the CloudKind enumeration.

DerivedEntities.Name: Cyclone
DerivedEntities.Description: A cyclone (or tropical cyclone), a rapidly-rotating storm system characterized by a low-pressure center, strong winds, and a spiral arrangement of thunderstorms that produce heavy rain.

DerivedEntities.Name: Hurricane
DerivedEntities.Description: A hurricane, a subtype of cyclone occurring in the North Atlantic Ocean or North-eastern Pacific Ocean whose intensity is measured using the Saffir-Simpson Hurricane Scale.

Attributes.Name: category
Attributes.Description: The hurricane's category during the time interval, using Saffir-Simpson Hurricane Wind Scale, a 1 to 5 rating based on a hurricane's sustained wind speed.

DerivedEntities.Name: TropicalCycloneAustralia
DerivedEntities.Description: A tropical cyclone, a subtype of cyclone that forms to the east of 90°E in the Southern Hemisphere whose intensity is measured by the Australian tropical cyclone intensity scale.

Attributes.Name: category
Attributes.Description:
Strength of tropical cyclone during the time interval, based on Australian Bureau of Meteorology Category System where:
1 - tropical cyclone, with typical gusts over flat land 90-125 km/h
2 - tropical cyclone, with typical gusts over flat land 125-164 km/h
3 - severe tropical cyclone, with typical gusts over flat land 165-224 km/h
4 - severe tropical cyclone, with typical gusts over flat land 225-279 km/h
5 - severe tropical cyclone, with typical gusts over flat land greater  than 280 km/h.

Attributes.Name: centralPressure
Attributes.Description: The central pressure of the cyclone during the time interval.

Attributes.Name: maxSurfaceWindSpeed
Attributes.Description: The maximum surface wind speed of the cyclone during the time interval.

Attributes.Name: windForce
Attributes.Description: Wind Force as classified on the Beaufort Scale (0-12) during the time interval.

DerivedEntities.Name: Tornado
DerivedEntities.Description: A tornado, a violent destructive whirling wind accompanied by a funnel-shaped cloud that progresses in a narrow path over the land.

Attributes.Name: fScale
Attributes.Description: Fujita scale (referred to as EF-scale starting in 2007) for the tornado.

Attributes.Name: width
Attributes.Description: Width of the tornado during the time interval.

DerivedEntities.Name: VolcanicAshCloud
DerivedEntities.Description: An ash cloud formed as a result of a volcanic eruption.

Attributes.Name: particleSize
Attributes.Description: The diameter of the particles during the time interval.

Attributes.Name: density
Attributes.Description: Particulate density of the ash cloud during the time interval.

Attributes.Name: base
Attributes.Description: The base altitude of the phenomenon.

Attributes.Name: maxCoverage
Attributes.Description: The maximum percentage coverage

Attributes.Name: speed
Attributes.Description: The speed of the phenomenon

Attributes.Name: altitude
Attributes.Description: The maximum altitude of the phenomenon.

Attributes.Name: direction
Attributes.Description: The direction the phenomenon is moving.

Attributes.Name: minCoverage
Attributes.Description: The minimum percentage coverage

DerivedEntities.Name: GeosphericPhenomenon
DerivedEntities.Description: A geospheric phenomenon.

DerivedEntities.Name: Earthquake
DerivedEntities.Description: An earthquake.

Attributes.Name: focalDepth
Attributes.Description: The depth below the earth's surface of the earthquake's focal point.

Attributes.Name: intensity
Attributes.Description: The intensity of the earthquake as defined by the Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI) scale. Possible values are 1-12, corresponding to I-XII.

Attributes.Name: magnitude
Attributes.Description: The magnitude of the earthquake as defined on the Moment Magnitude (M<sub>w</sub>) scale, which measures the size of earthquakes in terms of the energy released. Must be greater than zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: Fire
DerivedEntities.Description: A fire, often uncontrolled, covering an area of land which typically contains combustible vegetation. Associated location information is assumed to describe the total area burned as of a specified time.

DerivedEntities.Name: Landslide
DerivedEntities.Description: A landslide, a large mass of rocks and earth that suddenly and quickly moves down the side of a mountain or hill.

DerivedEntities.Name: LightningStrike
DerivedEntities.Description: A cloud-to-ground lightning strike at a particular location.

Attributes.Name: errorEllipseConfidence
Attributes.Description: Likelihood that strike fell within errorEllipse.

Attributes.Name: errorEllipseMinorSemiAxis
Attributes.Description: Length of minor semi-axis (shortest radius) of the error ellipse.

Attributes.Name: negativePolarity
Attributes.Description: The polarity of the strike, with T meaning negative. About 90% of all lightning strokes are negative strokes, meaning that they were initiated by a large concentration of negative charge in the cloud-base; this tends to induce an area of positive charge on the ground.

Attributes.Name: errorEllipseMajorSemiAxis
Attributes.Description: Length of major semi-axis (longest radius) of the error ellipse.

Attributes.Name: errorEllipseOrientation
Attributes.Description: The orientation of the major semi- axis in degrees from True North.

Attributes.Name: peakAmplitude
Attributes.Description: Peak current of strike.

DerivedEntities.Name: HydrosphericPhenomenon
DerivedEntities.Description: A hydrospheric phenomenon.

DerivedEntities.Name: Flood
DerivedEntities.Description: A flood, an overflowing of a large amount of water beyond its normal confines, esp. over what is normally dry land.

DerivedEntities.Name: Tsunami
DerivedEntities.Description: A tsunami (tidal wave), a long high sea wave caused by an earthquake, submarine landslide, or other disturbance.

Attributes.Name: intensity
Attributes.Description: Tsunami intensity on the Papadopoulos-Imamura tsunami intensity scale. Possible values are 1-12, corresponding to I-XII.

Attributes.Name: magnitude
Attributes.Description: Tsunami magnitude in the Tsunami Magnitude Scale (Mt).  Is greater than zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: Whirlpool
DerivedEntities.Description: A whirlpool, a rapidly rotating mass of water in a river or sea into which objects may be drawn, typically caused by the meeting of conflicting currents.

DerivedEntities.Name: SpacePhenomenon
DerivedEntities.Description: An extra-terrestrial phenomenon.

DerivedEntities.Name: MagneticStorm
DerivedEntities.Description: A magnetic storm, a temporary disturbance of the earth's magnetic field, induced by radiation and streams of charged particles from the sun.

Attributes.Name: changeDst
Attributes.Description:
Change in the disturbance  - storm time (Dst) index. The size of a geomagnetic storm is classified as:
- moderate ( -50 nT >minimum of Dst > -100 nT)
- intense (-100 nT > minimum Dst > -250 nT) or 
- super-storm ( minimum of Dst < -250 nT).

Attributes.Name: timeInterval
Attributes.Description: The timestamp of the phenomenon as a single point or time interval.

Entities.Name: EnvironmentalLocationType
Entities.Description: Type of environmental location. Used when an environmental alert or phenomenon has multiple locations associated with it.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: The kind of location. Typical values might be center, extent, primary, secondary, etc.

Entities.Name: FaultImpedance
Entities.Description: Impedance description for the fault.

Attributes.Name: rGround
Attributes.Description: The resistance of the fault between phases and ground.

Attributes.Name: rLineToLine
Attributes.Description: The resistance of the fault between phases.

Attributes.Name: xGround
Attributes.Description: The reactance of the fault between phases and ground.

Attributes.Name: xLineToLine
Attributes.Description: The reactance of the fault between phases.

Entities.Name: PhaseConnectedFaultKind
Entities.Description: The type of fault connection among phases.

Attributes.Name: lineToGround
Attributes.Description: The fault connects the indicated phases to ground. The line to line fault impedance is not used and assumed infinite. The full ground impedance is connected between each phase specified in the fault and ground, but not between the phases.

Attributes.Name: lineToLine
Attributes.Description: The fault connects the specified phases together without a connection to ground. The ground impedance of this fault is ignored. The line to line impedance is connected between each of the phases specified in the fault. For example three times for a three phase fault, one time for a two phase fault.  A single phase fault should not be specified.

Attributes.Name: lineToLineToGround
Attributes.Description: The fault connects the indicated phases to ground and to each other. The line to line impedance is connected between each of the phases specified in the fault in a full mesh. For example three times for a three phase fault, one time for a two phase fault. A single phase fault should not be specified. The full ground impedance is connected between each phase specified in the fault and ground.

Attributes.Name: lineOpen
Attributes.Description: The fault is when the conductor path is broken between two terminals. Additional coexisting faults may be required if the broken conductor also causes connections to grounds or other lines or phases.

Entities.Name: ContingencyEquipmentStatusKind
Entities.Description: Indicates the state which the contingency equipment is to be in when the contingency is applied.

Attributes.Name: inService
Attributes.Description: The equipment is to be put into service.

Attributes.Name: outOfService
Attributes.Description: The equipment is to be taken out of service.

Entities.Name: ControlAreaSolutionData
Entities.Description: State Estimator Solution Pool Interchange and Losses.

Attributes.Name: solvedInterchange
Attributes.Description:
Pool MW Interchange 
Attribute Usage: The active power interchange of the pool

Attributes.Name: solvedLosses

Entities.Name: TREntitlement
Entities.Description:
A Transmission Right(TR) can be a chain of TR's or on individual. 

When a transmission right is not a chain, this is formally the ETC/TOR Entitlement for each ETC/TOR contract with the inclusion of CVR(Converted Rights) as an ETC. This is the sum of all entitlements on all related transmission interfaces for the same TR.

When TR is a chain, its entitlement is the minimum of all entitlements for the individual TRs in the chain.

Entities.Name: MarketRoleKind
Entities.Description: Kind of market role an organisation can have. This list is not exhausted, as other roles may exist.

Attributes.Name: distributionProvider
Attributes.Description: Distribution provider.

Attributes.Name: purchasingSellingEntity
Attributes.Description: Purchasing selling entity.

Attributes.Name: reliabilityAuthority
Attributes.Description: Reliability authority.

Attributes.Name: interchangeAuthority
Attributes.Description: Interchange authority.

Attributes.Name: transmissionPlanner
Attributes.Description: Transmission planner.

Attributes.Name: complianceMonitor
Attributes.Description: Compliance monitor.

Attributes.Name: BillingAgent
Attributes.Description: The party responsible for invoicing a concerned party.

Attributes.Name: BlockEnergyTrader
Attributes.Description: A party that is selling or buying energy on a firm basis (a fixed volume per market time period).

Attributes.Name: Consumer
Attributes.Description: A party that consumes electricity. Additional information: This is a Type of Party Connected to the Grid.

Attributes.Name: ConsumptionResponsibleParty
Attributes.Description: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between enegry nominated and consumed for all associated Accounting Points. Additional information: This is a type of Balance Responsible Party.

Attributes.Name: CoordinationCenterOperator
Attributes.Description:
Responsible for :
1. The coordination of exchange programs between its related Control Blocks and for the exchanges between its associated Coordination Center Zones.
2. Ensuring that its Control Blocks respect their obligations in respect to load frequency control.
3. Calculating the time deviation in cooperation with the associated coordination centers.
4. Carrying out the settlement and/or compensation between its Control Blocks and against the other Coordination Center Zones.

Attributes.Name: GridAccessProvider
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for providing access to the grid through an Accounting Point and its use for energy consumption or production to the Party Connected to the Grid.

Attributes.Name: InterconnectionTradeResponsible
Attributes.Description: Is a Balance Responsible Party or depends on one. They are recognized by the Nomination Validator for the nomination of already allocated capacity. Additional information: This is a type of Balance Responsible Party.

Attributes.Name: MarketInformationAggregator
Attributes.Description: Market Information Aggregator, A party that provides market related information that has been compiled from the figures supplied by different actors in the market. This information may also be published or distributed for general use. Note: The Market Information Aggregator may receive information from any market participant that is relevant for publication or distribution.

Attributes.Name: MeterOperator
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for installing, maintaining, testing, certifying and decommissioning physical meters.

Attributes.Name: MeteredDataCollector
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for meter reading and quality control of the reading.

Attributes.Name: MeteringPointAdministrator
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for registering the parties linked to the metering points in a Metering Grid Area. They are also responsible for maintaining the Metering Point technical specifications. They are responsible for creating and terminating metering points.

Attributes.Name: MOLResponsible
Attributes.Description: Responsible for the management of the available tenders for all Acquiring System Operators to establish the order of the reserve capacity that can be activated.

Attributes.Name: ReconciliationAccountable
Attributes.Description: A party that is financially accountable for the reconciled volume of energy products for a profiled Accounting Point.

Attributes.Name: ReconciliationResponsible
Attributes.Description:
A party that is responsible for reconciling, within a Metering Grid Area, the volumes used in the imbalance settlement process for profiled Accounting Points and the actual metered quantities.
Note:
The Reconciliation Responsible may delegate the invoicing responsibility to a more generic role such as a Billing Agent.

Attributes.Name: ReserveAllocator
Attributes.Description: Informs the market of reserve requirements, receives tenders against the requirements and in compliance with the prequalification criteria, determines what tenders meet requirements and assigns tenders.

Attributes.Name: ResourceProvider
Attributes.Description: A role that manages a resource object and provides the schedules for it

Attributes.Name: energyServiceConsumer
Attributes.Description: Energy service consumer.

Attributes.Name: generatorOwner
Attributes.Description: Generator merchant owner.

Attributes.Name: generatorOperator
Attributes.Description: Generator merchant operator.

Attributes.Name: transmissionServiceProvider
Attributes.Description: Transmission service provider.

Attributes.Name: transmissionOwner
Attributes.Description: Transmission owner.

Attributes.Name: transmissionOperator
Attributes.Description: Transmission operator.

Attributes.Name: loadServingEntity
Attributes.Description: Load serving entity.

Attributes.Name: competitiveRetailer
Attributes.Description: Competitive retailer.

Attributes.Name: planningAuthority
Attributes.Description: Planning authority.

Attributes.Name: balancingAuthority
Attributes.Description: Balancing authority.

Attributes.Name: resourcePlanner
Attributes.Description: Resource planner.

Attributes.Name: standardsDeveloper
Attributes.Description: Standards developer.

Attributes.Name: BalanceResponsibleParty
Attributes.Description: A party that has a contract proving financial security and identifying balance responsibility with the Imbalance Settlement Responsible of the Market Balance Area entitling the party to operate in the market. This is the only role allowing a party to nominate energy on a wholesale level. Additional information: The meaning of the word "balance" in this context signifies that the quantity contracted to provide or to consume shall be equal to the quantity really provided or consumed. Equivalent to "Program responsible party" in the Netherlands. Equivalent to "Balance group manager" in Germany. Equivalent to "market agent" in Spain.

Attributes.Name: BalanceSupplier
Attributes.Description: A party that markets the difference between actual metered energy consumption and the energy bought with firm energy contracts by the Party Connected to the Grid. In addition the Balance Supplier markets any difference with the firm energy contract (of the Party Connected to the Grid) and the metered production. Additional information: There is only one Balance Supplier for each Accounting Point.

Attributes.Name: CapacityCoordinator
Attributes.Description: A party, acting on behalf of the System Operators involved, responsible for establishing a coordinated Offered Capacity and/or Net Transfer Capacity (NTC) and/or Available Transfer Capacity (ATC) between several Market Balance Areas.

Attributes.Name: CapacityTrader
Attributes.Description:
A party that has a contract to participate in the Capacity Market to acquire capacity through a Transmission Capacity Allocator.

The capacity may be acquired on behalf of an Interconnection Trade Responsible or for sale on secondary capacity markets.

Attributes.Name: ControlAreaOperator
Attributes.Description:
Responsible for :
1. The coordination of exchange programs between its related Market Balance Areas and for the exchanges between its associated Control Areas.
2. The load frequency control for its own area.
3. The coordination of the correction of time deviations.

Attributes.Name: ControlBlockOperator
Attributes.Description:
Responsible for :
1. The coordination of exchanges between its associated Control Blocks and the organisation of the coordination of exchange programs between its related Control Areas.
2. The load frequency control within its own block and ensuring that its Control Areas respect their obligations in respect to load frequency control and time deviation.
3. The organisation of the settlement and/or compensation between its Control Areas.

Attributes.Name: GridOperator
Attributes.Description: A party that operates one or more grids.

Attributes.Name: ImbalanceSettlementResponsible
Attributes.Description:
A party that is responsible for settlement of the difference between the contracted quantities and the realised quantities of energy products for the Balance Responsible Parties in a Market Balance Area.
Note:
The Imbalance Settlement Responsible has not the responsibility to invoice. The Imbalance Settlement Responsible may delegate the invoicing responsibility to a more generic role such as a Billing Agent.

Attributes.Name: MarketOperator
Attributes.Description: The unique power exchange of trades for the actual delivery of energy that receives the bids from the Balance Responsible Parties that have a contract to bid. The Market Operator determines the market energy price for the Market Balance Area after applying technical constraints from the System Operator. It may also establish the price for the reconciliation within a Metering Grid Area.

Attributes.Name: MeterAdministrator
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for keeping a database of meters.

Attributes.Name: MeteredDataResponsible
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for the establishment and validation of metered data based on the collected data received from the Metered Data Collector. The party is responsible for the history of metered data for a Metering Point.

Attributes.Name: MeteredDataAggregator
Attributes.Description: A party responsible for the establishment and qualification of metered data from the Metered Data Responsible. This data is aggregated according to a defined set of market rules.

Attributes.Name: NominationValidator
Attributes.Description: Has the responsibility of ensuring that all capacity nominated is within the allowed limits and confirming all valid nominations to all involved parties. They inform the Interconnection Trade Responsible of the maximum nominated capacity allowed. Depending on market rules for a given interconnection the corresponding System Operators may appoint one Nomination Validator.

Attributes.Name: PartyConnectedToTheGrid
Attributes.Description: A party that contracts for the right to consume or produce electricity at an Accounting Point.

Attributes.Name: Producer
Attributes.Description: A party that produces electricity. Additional information: This is a type of Party Connected to the Grid.

Attributes.Name: ProductionResponsibleParty
Attributes.Description: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy nominated and produced for all associated Accounting Points. Additional information: This is a type of Balance Responsible Party.

Attributes.Name: SchedulingCoordinator
Attributes.Description: A party that is responsible for the schedule information and its exchange on behalf of a Balance Responsible Party. For example in the Polish market a Scheduling Coordinator is responsible for information interchange for scheduling and settlement.

Attributes.Name: SystemOperator
Attributes.Description: A party that is responsible for a stable power system operation (including the organisation of physical balance) through a transmission grid in a geographical area. The System Operator will also determine and be responsible for cross border capacity and exchanges. If necessary they may reduce allocated capacity to ensure operational stability. Transmission as mentioned above means "the transport of electricity on the extra high or high voltage network with a view to its delivery to final customers or to distributors. Operation of transmission includes as well the tasks of system operation concerning its management of energy flows, reliability of the system and availability of all necessary system services." (definition taken from the ENTSO-E RGCE Operation handbook Glossary). Note: additional obligations may be imposed through local market rules.

Attributes.Name: TradeResponsibleParty
Attributes.Description: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy nominated and consumed for all associated Accounting Points. Note: A power exchange without any privileged responsibilities acts as a Trade Responsible Party. Additional information: This is a type of Balance Responsible Party.

Attributes.Name: TransmissionCapacityAllocator
Attributes.Description: Manages the allocation of transmission capacity for an Allocated Capacity Area. For explicit auctions: The Transmission Capacity Allocator manages, on behalf of the System Operators, the allocation of available transmission capacity for an Allocated capacity Area. They offer the available transmission capacity to the market, allocates the available transmission capacity to individual Capacity Traders and calculates the billing amount of already allocated capacities to the Capacity Traders.

Entities.Name: OperatingShare
Entities.Description: Specifies the operations contract relationship between a power system resource and a contract participant.

Attributes.Name: percentage
Attributes.Description: Percentage operational ownership between the pair (power system resource and operating participant) associated with this share. The total percentage ownership for a power system resource should add to 100%.

Entities.Name: RegularTimePoint
Entities.Description: Time point for a schedule where the time between the consecutive points is constant.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: The position of the regular time point in the sequence. Note that time points don't have to be sequential, i.e. time points may be omitted. The actual time for a RegularTimePoint is computed by multiplying the associated regular interval schedule's time step with the regular time point sequence number and adding the associated schedules start time. To specify values for the start time, use sequence number 0.  The sequence number cannot be negative.

Attributes.Name: value1
Attributes.Description: The first value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

Attributes.Name: value2
Attributes.Description: The second value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

Entities.Name: IdentifiedObject
Entities.Description: This is a root class to provide common identification for all classes needing identification and naming attributes.

DerivedEntities.Name: ACDCTerminal
DerivedEntities.Description: An electrical connection point (AC or DC) to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called connectivity nodes.

DerivedEntities.Name: DCBaseTerminal
DerivedEntities.Description: An electrical connection point at a piece of DC conducting equipment. DC terminals are connected at one physical DC node that may have multiple DC terminals connected. A DC node is similar to an AC connectivity node. The model requires that DC connections are distinct from AC connections.

DerivedEntities.Name: ACDCConverterDCTerminal
DerivedEntities.Description: A DC electrical connection point at the AC/DC converter. The AC/DC converter is electrically connected also to the AC side. The AC connection is inherited from the AC conducting equipment in the same way as any other AC equipment. The AC/DC converter DC terminal is separate from generic DC terminal to restrict the connection with the AC side to AC/DC converter and so that no other DC conducting equipment can be connected to the AC side.

Attributes.Name: polarity
Attributes.Description:
Represents the normal network polarity condition. Depending on the converter configuration the value shall be set as follows:
- For a monopole with two converter terminals use DCPolarityKind “positive” and “negative”.
- For a bi-pole or symmetric monopole with three converter terminals use DCPolarityKind “positive”, “middle” and “negative”.

DerivedEntities.Name: DCTerminal
DerivedEntities.Description: An electrical connection point to generic DC conducting equipment.

DerivedEntities.Name: Terminal
DerivedEntities.Description: An AC electrical connection point to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called connectivity nodes.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktTerminal
DerivedEntities.Description: Subclass of IEC61970:Core:Terminal.

Attributes.Name: phases
Attributes.Description:
Represents the normal network phasing condition. If the attribute is missing, three phases (ABC) shall be assumed, except for terminals of grounding classes (specializations of EarthFaultCompensator, GroundDisconnector, GroundSwitch, and Ground) which will be assumed to be N. Therefore, phase code ABCN is explicitly declared when needed, e.g. for star point grounding equipment.
The phase code on terminals connecting same ConnectivityNode or same TopologicalNode as well as for equipment between two terminals shall be consistent.

Attributes.Name: connected
Attributes.Description:
The connected status is related to a bus-branch model and the topological node to terminal relation.  True implies the terminal is connected to the related topological node and false implies it is not. 
In a bus-branch model, the connected status is used to tell if equipment is disconnected without having to change the connectivity described by the topological node to terminal relation. A valid case is that conducting equipment can be connected in one end and open in the other. In particular for an AC line segment, where the reactive line charging can be significant, this is a relevant case.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: The orientation of the terminal connections for a multiple terminal conducting equipment.  The sequence numbering starts with 1 and additional terminals should follow in increasing order.   The first terminal is the "starting point" for a two terminal branch.

DerivedEntities.Name: ActivityRecord
DerivedEntities.Description: Records activity for an entity at a point in time; activity may be for an event that has already occurred or for a planned activity.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetHealthEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: An asset health-related event that is created by an analytic. The event is a record of a change in asset health.

Attributes.Name: effectiveDateTime
Attributes.Description: The date and time when the event is effective.

Attributes.Name: actionRecommendation
Attributes.Description: Recommendation for action.

Attributes.Name: actionTimeline
Attributes.Description: Time horizon for action.

DerivedEntities.Name: ComplianceEvent
DerivedEntities.Description:
Compliance events are used for reporting regulatory or contract compliance issues and/or variances. These might be created as a consequence of local business processes and associated rules. It is anticipated that this class will be customised extensively to meet local implementation needs.
Use inherited 'type' to indicate that, for example, expected performance will not be met or reported as mandated.

Attributes.Name: deadline
Attributes.Description: The deadline for compliance.

DerivedEntities.Name: ConfigurationEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: Used to report details on creation, change or deletion of an entity or its configuration.

Attributes.Name: effectiveDateTime
Attributes.Description: Date and time this event has or will become effective.

Attributes.Name: modifiedBy
Attributes.Description: Source/initiator of modification.

Attributes.Name: remark
Attributes.Description: Free text remarks.

DerivedEntities.Name: EndDeviceEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: Event detected by a device function associated with the end device.

Attributes.Name: issuerID
Attributes.Description: Unique identifier of the business entity originating an end device control.

Attributes.Name: issuerTrackingID
Attributes.Description: Identifier assigned by the initiator (e.g. retail electric provider) of an end device control action to uniquely identify the demand response event, text message, or other subject of the control action. Can be used when cancelling an event or text message request or to identify the originating event or text message in a consequential end device event.

Attributes.Name: userID
Attributes.Description: (if user initiated) ID of user who initiated this end device event.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnvironmentalAlert
DerivedEntities.Description: An environmental alert issued by a provider or system.

Attributes.Name: alertType
Attributes.Description: The type of the issued alert which is drawn from the specified alert type list.

Attributes.Name: cancelledDateTime
Attributes.Description: Time and date alert cancelled. Used only if alert is cancelled before it expires.

Attributes.Name: headline
Attributes.Description:
An abbreviated textual description of the alert issued. 
Note: the full text of the alert appears in the .description attribute (inherited from IdentifiedObject).

Attributes.Name: inEffect
Attributes.Description: The interval for which this weather alert is in effect.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnvironmentalEvent
DerivedEntities.Description:
An environmental event to which one or more forecasts or observations may be tied and which may relate to or affect one or more assets. This class is intended to be used as a means of grouping forecasts and/or observations and could be used for a variety of purposes, including:
  • to define a 'named' event like Hurricane Katrina and allow the historic (or forecast) values for phenomena and measurements (precipitation, temperature) across time to be associated with it
  • to identify assets that were (or are forecast to be) affected by a phenomenon or set of measurements

DerivedEntities.Name: FailureEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: An event where an asset has failed to perform its functions within specified parameters. This class is intended to reflect the failure itself. Additional information resulting from forensic analysis could be captured by a diagnosis data set.

Attributes.Name: breakerFailureReason
Attributes.Description: Reason for breaker failure.

Attributes.Name: failureClassification
Attributes.Description: Classification of failure.

Attributes.Name: failureIsolationMethod
Attributes.Description: How the asset failure was isolated from the system.

Attributes.Name: failureMode
Attributes.Description: What asset failed to be able to do.

Attributes.Name: location
Attributes.Description: Failure location on an object.

Attributes.Name: transformerFailureReason
Attributes.Description: Reason for transformer failure.

Attributes.Name: corporateCode
Attributes.Description: Code for asset failure.

Attributes.Name: failureDateTime
Attributes.Description: Time and date of asset failure.

Attributes.Name: faultLocatingMethod
Attributes.Description: The method used for locating the faulted part of the asset. For example, cable options include: Cap Discharge-Thumping, Bridge Method, Visual Inspection, Other.

Attributes.Name: rootCause
Attributes.Description: Root cause of asset failure.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktActivityRecord
DerivedEntities.Description: Subclass of IEC61968: Common:ActivityRecord.

DerivedEntities.Name: PSREvent
DerivedEntities.Description: Event recording the change in operational status of a power system resource; may be for an event that has already occurred or for a planned activity.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of event.

DerivedEntities.Name: SwitchingEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: Event indicating the completion (success or fail) of any switching action (jumper action, cut action, tag action, etc).  The switching action may or may not be a consequential event in response to a request to complete the action.

DerivedEntities.Name: WorkActivityRecord
DerivedEntities.Description: Records information about the status of work or work task at a point in time.

Attributes.Name: percentComplete
Attributes.Description: Estimated percentage of completion of this individual work task or overall work order.

Attributes.Name: createdDateTime
Attributes.Description: Date and time this activity record has been created (different from the 'status.dateTime', which is the time of a status change of the associated object, if applicable).

Attributes.Name: reason
Attributes.Description: Reason for event resulting in this activity record, typically supplied when user initiated.

Attributes.Name: severity
Attributes.Description: Severity level of event resulting in this activity record.

Attributes.Name: status
Attributes.Description: Information on consequence of event resulting in this activity record.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: Type of event resulting in this activity record.

DerivedEntities.Name: AdjacentCASet
DerivedEntities.Description: Groups Adjacent Control Areas.

Attributes.Name: lossPercentage
Attributes.Description: Loss percentage

DerivedEntities.Name: AggregateNode
DerivedEntities.Description: An aggregated node can define a typed grouping further defined by the AnodeType enumeratuion. Types range from System Zone/Regions to Market Energy Regions to Aggregated Loads and Aggregated Generators.

DerivedEntities.Name: LoadAggregationPoint
DerivedEntities.Description: A specialized class of type AggregatedNode type. Defines Load Aggregation Points.

DerivedEntities.Name: MarketRegion
DerivedEntities.Description: A specialized class of AggregatedNode type. Defines the MarketRegions. Regions could be system Market Regions, Energy Regions or Ancillary Service Regions.

DerivedEntities.Name: MSSZone
DerivedEntities.Description: Model to define a zone within a Metered Sub System.

Attributes.Name: ignoreLosses
Attributes.Description: Provides an indication if losses are to be ignored for this metered subsystem zone.

Attributes.Name: lossFactor
Attributes.Description: This is the default loss factor for the Metered Sub-System (MSS) zone. The actual losses are calculated during the RT market.

Attributes.Name: rucGrossSettlement
Attributes.Description: Metered Sub-System (MSS) Load Following may select Net vs. Gross settlement.  Net Settlement requires the net Demand settled at the Metered Sub-Sustem (MSS) Load Aggregation Point (LAP) and Net Supply needs to settle at the equivalent to the weighted average price of the MSS generation.  Gross load will be settled at the System LAP and the Gross supply will be settled at the LMP.  MSS Aggregation that elects gross settlement shall have to identify if its resources are Load Following or not.

DerivedEntities.Name: RUCZone
DerivedEntities.Description: A specialized class of type AggregatedNode type. Defines RUC Zones. A forecast region represents a collection of Nodes for which the Market operator has developed sufficient historical demand and relevant weather data to perform a demand forecast for such area. The Market Operator may further adjust this forecast to ensure that the Reliability Unit Commitment produces adequate local capacity procurement.

Attributes.Name: anodeType
Attributes.Description: Type of aggregated node

Attributes.Name: qualifASOrder
Attributes.Description: Processing Order for AS self-provisions for this region. The priority of this attribute directs the awards of any resource that resides in overlapping regions. The regions are processed in priority manner.

DerivedEntities.Name: AlertTypeList
DerivedEntities.Description:
A named list of alert types.
Note:  the name of the list is reflected in the .name attribute (inherited from IdentifiedObject).

Attributes.Name: version
Attributes.Description: The version of the named list of alert types.

DerivedEntities.Name: AltGeneratingUnitMeas
DerivedEntities.Description: A prioritized measurement to be used for the generating unit in the control area specification.

Attributes.Name: priority
Attributes.Description: Priority of a measurement usage.   Lower numbers have first priority.

DerivedEntities.Name: AltTieMeas
DerivedEntities.Description: A prioritized measurement to be used for the tie flow as part of the control area specification.

Attributes.Name: priority
Attributes.Description: Priority of a measurement usage.   Lower numbers have first priority.

DerivedEntities.Name: AnalyticScore
DerivedEntities.Description: An indicative scoring by an analytic that can be used to characterize the health of or the risk associated with one or more assets.  The analytic score reflects the results of an execution of an analytic against an asset or group of assets.

DerivedEntities.Name: AggregateScore
DerivedEntities.Description: An aggregated indicative scoring by an analytic, which is based on other analytic scores, that can be used to characterize the health of or the risk associated with one or more assets.

DerivedEntities.Name: HealthScore
DerivedEntities.Description: Score that is indicative of the health of one or more assets.

DerivedEntities.Name: RiskScore
DerivedEntities.Description: Score that is indicative of the risk associated with one or more assets.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: The risk kind, such as CustomerRisk, FinancialRisk, SafetyRisk, etc.

Attributes.Name: effectiveDateTime
Attributes.Description: Date-time for when the score applies.

Attributes.Name: calculationDateTime
Attributes.Description: Timestamp of when the score was calculated.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: Asset health score value.

DerivedEntities.Name: Appointment
DerivedEntities.Description: Meeting time and location.

Attributes.Name: callAhead
Attributes.Description: True if requested to call customer when someone is about to arrive at their premises.

Attributes.Name: meetingInterval
Attributes.Description: Date and time reserved for appointment.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssemblyDescription
DerivedEntities.Description: A description for how to assemble model parts for a specific purpose.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssemblyManifest
DerivedEntities.Description: A collection of model parts when combined form a case or part of a case.

DerivedEntities.Name: Asset
DerivedEntities.Description: Tangible resource of the utility, including power system equipment, various end devices, cabinets, buildings, etc. For electrical network equipment, the role of the asset is defined through PowerSystemResource and its subclasses, defined mainly in the Wires model (refer to IEC61970-301 and model package IEC61970::Wires). Asset description places emphasis on the physical characteristics of the equipment fulfilling that role.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetContainer
DerivedEntities.Description: Asset that is aggregation of other assets such as conductors, transformers, switchgear, land, fences, buildings, equipment, vehicles, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: Cabinet
DerivedEntities.Description: Enclosure that offers protection to the equipment it contains and/or safety to people/animals outside it.

DerivedEntities.Name: DuctBank
DerivedEntities.Description: A duct contains individual wires in the layout as specified with associated wire spacing instances; number of them gives the number of conductors in this duct.

Attributes.Name: circuitCount
Attributes.Description: Number of circuits in duct bank. Refer to associations between a duct (ConductorAsset) and an ACLineSegment to understand which circuits are in which ducts.

DerivedEntities.Name: EndDevice
DerivedEntities.Description:
Asset container that performs one or more end device functions. One type of end device is a meter which can perform metering, load management, connect/disconnect, accounting functions, etc. Some end devices, such as ones monitoring and controlling air conditioners, refrigerators, pool pumps may be connected to a meter. All end devices may have communication capability defined by the associated communication function(s). An end device may be owned by a consumer, a service provider, utility or otherwise.
There may be a related end device function that identifies a sensor or control point within a metering application or communications systems (e.g., water, gas, electricity).
Some devices may use an optical port that conforms to the ANSI C12.18 standard for communications.

DerivedEntities.Name: Meter
DerivedEntities.Description: Physical asset that performs the metering role of the usage point. Used for measuring consumption and detection of events.

Attributes.Name: connectionCategory
Attributes.Description: A code used to specify the connection category, e.g. low voltage, where the meter operates.

Attributes.Name: formNumber
Attributes.Description: Meter form designation per ANSI C12.10 or other applicable standard. An alphanumeric designation denoting the circuit arrangement for which the meter is applicable and its specific terminal arrangement.

Attributes.Name: amrSystem
Attributes.Description: Automated meter reading (AMR) or other communication system responsible for communications to this end device.

Attributes.Name: installCode
Attributes.Description: Installation code.

Attributes.Name: isPan
Attributes.Description: If true, this is a premises area network (PAN) device.

Attributes.Name: isVirtual
Attributes.Description: If true, there is no physical device. As an example, a virtual meter can be defined to aggregate the consumption for two or more physical meters. Otherwise, this is a physical hardware device.

Attributes.Name: timeZoneOffset
Attributes.Description: Time zone offset relative to GMT for the location of this end device.

DerivedEntities.Name: Facility
DerivedEntities.Description: A facility may contain buildings, storage facilities, switching facilities, power generation, manufacturing facilities, maintenance facilities, etc.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of this facility.

DerivedEntities.Name: Structure
DerivedEntities.Description: Construction holding assets such as conductors, transformers, switchgear, etc. Where applicable, number of conductors can be derived from the number of associated wire spacing instances.

DerivedEntities.Name: Pole
DerivedEntities.Description: Pole asset.

Attributes.Name: jpaReference
Attributes.Description: Joint pole agreement reference number.

Attributes.Name: preservativeKind
Attributes.Description: Kind of preservative for this pole.

Attributes.Name: treatedDateTime
Attributes.Description: Date and time pole was last treated with preservative.

Attributes.Name: baseKind
Attributes.Description: Kind of base for this pole.

Attributes.Name: breastBlock
Attributes.Description: True if a block of material has been attached to base of pole in ground for stability. This technique is used primarily when anchors can not be used.

Attributes.Name: classification
Attributes.Description: Pole class: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, H1, H2, Other, Unknown.

Attributes.Name: construction
Attributes.Description: The framing structure mounted on the pole.

Attributes.Name: diameter
Attributes.Description: Diameter of the pole.

Attributes.Name: length
Attributes.Description: Length of the pole (inclusive of any section of the pole that may be underground post-installation).

Attributes.Name: speciesType
Attributes.Description: Pole species. Aluminum, Aluminum Davit, Concrete, Fiberglass, Galvanized Davit, Galvanized, Steel Davit Primed, Steel Davit, Steel Standard Primed, Steel, Truncated, Wood-Treated, Wood-Hard, Wood-Salt Treated, Wood-Soft, Wood, Other, Unknown.

Attributes.Name: treatmentKind
Attributes.Description: Kind of treatment for this pole.

DerivedEntities.Name: Tower
DerivedEntities.Description:
Tower asset. Dimensions of the Tower are specified in associated DimensionsInfo class.
When used for planning purposes, a transmission tower carrying two 3-phase circuits will have 2 instances of Connection, each of which will have 3 MountingPoint instances, one for each phase all with coordinates relative to a common origin on the tower. (It may also have a 3rd Connection with a single MountingPoint for the Neutral line).

Attributes.Name: constructionKind
Attributes.Description: Construction structure on the tower.

DerivedEntities.Name: UndergroundStructure
DerivedEntities.Description: Underground structure.

Attributes.Name: hasVentilation
Attributes.Description: True if vault is ventilating.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: True if vault is ventilating.

Attributes.Name: material
Attributes.Description: Primary material of underground structure.

Attributes.Name: sealingWarrantyExpiresDate
Attributes.Description: Date sealing warranty expires.

Attributes.Name: fumigantAppliedDate
Attributes.Description: Date fumigant was last applied.

Attributes.Name: removeWeed
Attributes.Description: True if weeds are to be removed around asset.

Attributes.Name: fumigantName
Attributes.Description: Name of fumigant.

Attributes.Name: height
Attributes.Description: Visible height of structure above ground level for overhead construction (e.g., Pole or Tower) or below ground level for an underground vault, manhole, etc. Refer to associated DimensionPropertiesInfo for other types of dimensions.

Attributes.Name: weedRemovedDate
Attributes.Description: Date weed were last removed.

Attributes.Name: ratedVoltage
Attributes.Description: Maximum rated voltage of the equipment that can be mounted on/contained within the structure.

Attributes.Name: materialKind
Attributes.Description: Material this structure is made of.

DerivedEntities.Name: Bushing
DerivedEntities.Description: Bushing asset.

DerivedEntities.Name: ComMedia
DerivedEntities.Description: Communication media such as fibre optic cable, power-line, telephone, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: ComModule
DerivedEntities.Description: An asset having communications capabilities that can be paired with a meter or other end device to provide the device with communication ability, through associated communication function. An end device that has communications capabilities through embedded hardware can use that function directly (without the communication module), or combine embedded communication function with additional communication functions provided through an external communication module (e.g. zigbee).

Attributes.Name: amrSystem
Attributes.Description: Automated meter reading (AMR) system communicating with this com module.

Attributes.Name: supportsAutonomousDst
Attributes.Description: If true, autonomous daylight saving time (DST) function is supported.

Attributes.Name: timeZoneOffset
Attributes.Description: Time zone offset relative to GMT for the location of this com module.

DerivedEntities.Name: FACTSDevice
DerivedEntities.Description: FACTS device asset.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of FACTS device.

DerivedEntities.Name: InterrupterUnit
DerivedEntities.Description:
Breaker interrupter.
Some interrupters have one fixed and one moving contact, some have 2 fixed contacts, some 2 moving contacts. An interrupter will have relationships with 2 bushings and those relationships may be any combination of the FixedContact and MovingContact associations.

DerivedEntities.Name: ConnectDisconnectFunction
DerivedEntities.Description: A function that will disconnect and reconnect the customer's load under defined conditions.

Attributes.Name: eventCount
Attributes.Description: Running cumulative count of connect or disconnect events, for the lifetime of this function or until the value is cleared.

Attributes.Name: isConnected
Attributes.Description: True if this function is in the connected state.

Attributes.Name: isDelayedDiscon
Attributes.Description: If set true, the switch may disconnect the service at the end of a specified time delay after the disconnect signal has been given. If set false, the switch may disconnect the service immediately after the disconnect signal has been given. This is typically the case for over current circuit-breakers which are classified as either instantaneous or slow acting.

Attributes.Name: isLocalAutoDisconOp
Attributes.Description: If set true and if disconnection can be operated locally, the operation happens automatically. Otherwise it happens manually.

Attributes.Name: isLocalAutoReconOp
Attributes.Description: If set true and if reconnection can be operated locally, then the operation happens automatically. Otherwise, it happens manually.

Attributes.Name: isRemoteAutoDisconOp
Attributes.Description: If set true and if disconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens automatically. If set false and if disconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens manually.

Attributes.Name: isRemoteAutoReconOp
Attributes.Description: If set true and if reconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens automatically. If set false and if reconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens manually.

Attributes.Name: rcdInfo
Attributes.Description: Information on remote connect disconnect switch.

DerivedEntities.Name: SurgeArresterInfo
DerivedEntities.Description: Properties of surge arrester.

Attributes.Name: continuousOperatingVoltage
Attributes.Description: Maximum continuous power frequency voltage allowed on the surge arrester.

Attributes.Name: isPolymer
Attributes.Description: If true, the arrester has a polymer housing, porcelain otherwise.

Attributes.Name: lightningImpulseDischargeVoltage
Attributes.Description: Residual voltage during an 8x20 microsecond current impulse at the nominal discharge current level.

Attributes.Name: lineDischargeClass
Attributes.Description: Determines the arrester energy discharge capability.  Choices are limited to 0 (none) through 5 (highest) by IEC 60099. Classes 1..3 require a 10-kA nominal discharge current. Classes 4..5 require a 20-kA nominal discharge current. Lower nominal discharge currents must use class 0.

Attributes.Name: nominalDischargeCurrent
Attributes.Description: The lightning discharge current used to classify the arrester. Choices are limited to 1.5, 2.5, 5, 10, and 20 kA by IEC 60099.

Attributes.Name: pressureReliefClass
Attributes.Description: Fault current level at which all parts of the failed arrester lie within a circle prescribed by IEC 60099.

Attributes.Name: ratedVoltage
Attributes.Description: The temporary overvoltage (TOV) level at power frequency that the surge arrester withstands for 10 seconds.

Attributes.Name: steepFrontDischargeVoltage
Attributes.Description: Residual voltage during a current impulse with front time of 1 microsecond, and magnitude equal to the nominal discharge current level.

Attributes.Name: switchingImpulseDischargeVoltage
Attributes.Description: Residual voltage during a current impulse with front time of at least 30 microseconds, and magnitude specified in IEC 60099 for the line discharge class. Does not apply to line discharge class 0.

DerivedEntities.Name: CoolingPowerRating
DerivedEntities.Description:
There are often stages of power which are associated with stages of cooling. For instance, a transformer may be rated 121kV on the primary, 15kV on the secondary and 4kV on the tertiary winding. These are voltage ratings and the power ratings are generally the same for all three windings and independent of the voltage ratings, there are instances where the tertiary may have a lower power rating.
For example, for three stages, the power rating may be 15/20/25 MVA and the cooling is OA/FA/FOA. The 15 MVA rating goes with the OA cooling (Oil and Air cooling). This is called the self cooled rating as there are no external cooling enhancements. The 20 MVA rating goes with the FA cooling (Forced Air cooling), this means that when the fans are running and thus enhancing the cooling characteristics, the transformer can operate at a power level of 20 MVA. The 25 MVA rating goes with the FOA cooling (Forced Oil and Air cooling), this means that when the fans and pumps are running and thus enhancing the cooling characteristics even more than before, the transformer can operate at a power level of 25 MVA. This 15/20/25 MVA does not state how the power is split between the various windings. It may be 25 MVA input on the primary, 25 MVA output on the secondary and 0 MVA output on the tertiary. It may also operate at 25 MVA input on the primary, 17 MVA output on the secondary and 8 MVA output on the tertiary.

Attributes.Name: coolingKind
Attributes.Description: Kind of cooling system.

Attributes.Name: powerRating
Attributes.Description: The power rating associated with type of cooling specified for this stage.

Attributes.Name: stage
Attributes.Description: Stage of cooling and associated power rating.
