DerivedEntities.Description: This is a version of a part of a model.  New instances of this class with new identity are instantiated upon changes to the content of this class or changes to the associated data set.  Instances of this class are considered immutable.  The case audit trail can reference this immutable data to exactly reproduce a case.

DerivedEntities.Name: MPMTestCategory
DerivedEntities.Description: Provides a reference to the Market Power Mitigation test identifiers and methods for the results of the DA or RT markets. Specific data is the test identifier (Price, Conduct, or Impact) and the test method (System MPM, Local MPM, Alternate System MPM, or Alternate Local MPM).

Attributes.Name: purposeFlag
Attributes.Description:
Nature of threshold data:
'M' - Mitigation threshold
'R' - Reporting threshold

Attributes.Name: testIdentifier
Attributes.Description:
1 - Global Price Test
2 - Global Conduct Test
3 - Global Impact Test
4 - Local Price Test
5 - Local Conduct Test
6 - Local Impact Test

Attributes.Name: testMethod
Attributes.Description: The method of performing the market power monitoring. Examples are Normal (default) thresholds or Alternate thresholds.

DerivedEntities.Name: MSSAggregation
DerivedEntities.Description: Metered Sub-System aggregation of MSS Zones.

Attributes.Name: costRecovery
Attributes.Description: Charge for Emission Costs, Start Up Costs, or Minimum Load Costs.

Attributes.Name: grossSettlement
Attributes.Description: MSS Load Following may select Net vs. Gross settlement.  Net Settlement requires the net Demand settled at the MSS LAP and Net Supply needs to settle at the equivalent to the weighted average price of the MSS generation.  Gross load will be settled at the System LAP and the Gross supply will be settled at the LMP.  MSS Aggregation that elects gross settlement shall have to identify if its resources are Load Following or not.

Attributes.Name: ignoreLosses
Attributes.Description: Provides an indication if losses are to be ignored for this zone. Also refered to as Exclude Marginal Losses.

Attributes.Name: ignoreMarginalLosses
Attributes.Description: Provides an indication if marginal losses are to be ignored for this zone.

Attributes.Name: loadFollowing
Attributes.Description: Indication that this particular MSSA participates in the Load Following function.

Attributes.Name: rucProcurement
Attributes.Description: Indicates that RUC will be procured by the ISO or self provided.

DerivedEntities.Name: MutualCoupling
DerivedEntities.Description: This class represents the zero sequence line mutual coupling.

Attributes.Name: distance11
Attributes.Description: Distance to the start of the coupled region from the first line's terminal having sequence number equal to 1.

Attributes.Name: distance21
Attributes.Description: Distance to the start of coupled region from the second line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

Attributes.Name: g0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence mutual coupling shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence branch-to-branch mutual impedance coupling, reactance.

Attributes.Name: b0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence mutual coupling shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: distance12
Attributes.Description: Distance to the end of the coupled region from the first line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

Attributes.Name: distance22
Attributes.Description: Distance to the end of coupled region from the second line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence branch-to-branch mutual impedance coupling, resistance.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProjectChangeVersion
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes the status and the planned implementation of the associated change set into the as-built model.    New instances of this class with new identity are instantiated upon changes to the content of this class or changes to the associated change set.  Instances of this class are considered immutable.  The case audit trail can reference this immutable data to exactly reproduce a case.

Attributes.Name: comment
Attributes.Description: A user provided comment describing the changes in this version from the previous version.

Attributes.Name: effectiveDateTime
Attributes.Description: The date/time the change set is included in the model.

Attributes.Name: timeStamp
Attributes.Description: The date/time this version was finalized and thus made immutable.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProjectComponent
DerivedEntities.Description: Abstract class for both a network model project and network model change.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProject
DerivedEntities.Description: A grouping of network model change descriptions.  Primarily used to organize the phases of an overall project.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProjectChange
DerivedEntities.Description: Network model project change described by versions of an associated change set.  Has persistent identity over multiple versions of the associated change set.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProjectRelationship
DerivedEntities.Description: A relationship that assists humans and software building cases by assembling project changes in the correct sequence.  This class may be specialized to create specific types of relationships.

DerivedEntities.Name: ProjectAlternative
DerivedEntities.Description:
Project B is an alternative to project A.  Project A is the primary alternative.
Multiple project alternatives should not be selected into a single network study case.

DerivedEntities.Name: ProjectDependency
DerivedEntities.Description: Project A change sets should be applied before Project B during case creation.

DerivedEntities.Name: NetworkModelProjectState
DerivedEntities.Description: A network model project version state.  States are agreed upon by the exchange community.  Examples are "approved", "proposed", "withdrawn", "committed" etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperatingParticipant
DerivedEntities.Description: An operator of multiple power system resource objects. Note multple operating participants may operate the same power system resource object.   This can be used for modeling jointly owned units where each owner operates as a contractual share.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperationalLimit
DerivedEntities.Description:
A value and normal value associated with a specific kind of limit. 
The sub class value and normalValue attributes vary inversely to the associated OperationalLimitType.acceptableDuration (acceptableDuration for short).  
If a particular piece of equipment has multiple operational limits of the same kind (apparent power, current, etc.), the limit with the greatest acceptableDuration shall have the smallest limit value and the limit with the smallest acceptableDuration shall have the largest limit value.  Note: A large current can only be allowed to flow through a piece of equipment for a short duration without causing damage, but a lesser current can be allowed to flow for a longer duration.

DerivedEntities.Name: ActivePowerLimit
DerivedEntities.Description: Limit on active power flow.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: Value of active power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: normalValue
Attributes.Description: The normal value of active power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: ApparentPowerLimit
DerivedEntities.Description: Apparent power limit.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: The apparent power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: normalValue
Attributes.Description: The normal apparent power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: CurrentLimit
DerivedEntities.Description: Operational limit on current.

Attributes.Name: normalValue
Attributes.Description: The normal value for limit on current flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: Limit on current flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: VoltageLimit
DerivedEntities.Description:
Operational limit applied to voltage.
The use of operational VoltageLimit is preferred instead of limits defined at VoltageLevel. The operational VoltageLimits are used, if present.

Attributes.Name: normalValue
Attributes.Description: The normal limit on voltage. High or low limit nature of the limit depends upon the properties of the operational limit type. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: Limit on voltage. High or low limit nature of the limit depends upon the properties of the operational limit type. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperationalLimitSet
DerivedEntities.Description: A set of limits associated with equipment.  Sets of limits might apply to a specific temperature, or season for example. A set of limits may contain different severities of limit levels that would apply to the same equipment. The set may contain limits of different types such as apparent power and current limits or high and low voltage limits  that are logically applied together as a set.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperationalLimitType
DerivedEntities.Description: The operational meaning of a category of limits.

Attributes.Name: acceptableDuration
Attributes.Description: The nominal acceptable duration of the limit. Limits are commonly expressed in terms of the time limit for which the limit is normally acceptable. The actual acceptable duration of a specific limit may depend on other local factors such as temperature or wind speed. The attribute has meaning only if the flag isInfiniteDuration is set to false, hence it shall not be exchanged when isInfiniteDuration is set to true.

Attributes.Name: direction
Attributes.Description: The direction of the limit.

Attributes.Name: isInfiniteDuration
Attributes.Description: Defines if the operational limit type has infinite duration. If true, the limit has infinite duration. If false, the limit has definite duration which is defined by the attribute acceptableDuration.

DerivedEntities.Name: Organisation
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that might have roles as utility, contractor, supplier, manufacturer, customer, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: ControlAreaOperator
DerivedEntities.Description: Operates the Control Area. Approves and implements energy transactions. Verifies both Inter-Control Area and Intra-Control Area transactions for the power system  before granting approval (and implementing) the transactions.

DerivedEntities.Name: CustomerConsumer
DerivedEntities.Description: The energy buyer in the energy marketplace.

DerivedEntities.Name: GenerationProvider
DerivedEntities.Description: The energy seller in the energy marketplace.

DerivedEntities.Name: Marketer
DerivedEntities.Description: Matches buyers and sellers, and secures transmission (and other ancillary services) needed to complete the energy transaction.

DerivedEntities.Name: MarketParticipant
DerivedEntities.Description: An identification of a party acting in a electricity market business process. This class is used to identify organizations that can participate in market management and/or market operations.

DerivedEntities.Name: RTO
DerivedEntities.Description: Regional transmission operator.

DerivedEntities.Name: SchedulingCoordinator
DerivedEntities.Description: Market participants could be represented by Scheduling Coordinators (SCs) that are registered with the RTO/ISO. One participant could register multiple SCs with the RTO/ISO. Many market participants can do business with the RTO/ISO using a single SC. One SC could schedule multiple generators. A load scheduling point could be used by multiple SCs. Each SC could schedule load at multiple scheduling points. An inter-tie scheduling point can be used by multiple SCs. Each SC can schedule interchange at multiple inter-tie scheduling points.

Attributes.Name: creditFlag
Attributes.Description: Flag to indicate creditworthiness (Y, N)

Attributes.Name: creditStartEffectiveDate
Attributes.Description: Date that the scheduling coordinator becomes creditworthy.

Attributes.Name: lastModified
Attributes.Description: Indication of the last time this scheduling coordinator information was modified.

Attributes.Name: qualificationStatus
Attributes.Description: Scheduling coordinator qualification status, Qualified, Not Qualified, or Disqualified.

Attributes.Name: scid
Attributes.Description: This is the short name or Scheduling Coordinator ID field.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransmissionProvider
DerivedEntities.Description: Provider of  the transmission capacity (interconnecting wires between Generation and Consumption) required  to fulfill and Energy Transaction's energy exchange. Posts information for transmission paths and AvailableTransmissionCapacities  on a reservation node.  Buys and sells its products and services on the same reservation node.

Attributes.Name: electronicAddress
Attributes.Description: Electronic address.

Attributes.Name: phone2
Attributes.Description: Additional phone number.

Attributes.Name: streetAddress
Attributes.Description: Street address.

Attributes.Name: phone1
Attributes.Description: Phone number.

Attributes.Name: postalAddress
Attributes.Description: Postal address, potentially different than 'streetAddress' (e.g., another city).

DerivedEntities.Name: OrganisationRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Identifies a way in which an organisation may participate in the utility enterprise (e.g., customer, manufacturer, etc).

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetOrganisationRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Role an organisation plays with respect to asset.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetOwner
DerivedEntities.Description: Owner of the asset.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetTestLab
DerivedEntities.Description: Test lab that performs various types of testing related to assets.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetTestSampleTaker
DerivedEntities.Description: Identity of person/organization that took sample.

DerivedEntities.Name: AssetUser
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that is a user of the asset.

DerivedEntities.Name: Maintainer
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that maintains assets.

DerivedEntities.Name: Bank
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that is a commercial bank, agency, or other institution that offers a similar service.

Attributes.Name: bic
Attributes.Description: Bank identifier code as defined in ISO 9362; for use in countries wher IBAN is not yet in operation.

Attributes.Name: iban
Attributes.Description: International bank account number defined in ISO 13616; for countries where IBAN is not in operation, the existing BIC or SWIFT codes may be used instead (see ISO 9362).

DerivedEntities.Name: BusinessRole
DerivedEntities.Description: A business role that this organisation plays. A single organisation typically performs many functions, each one described as a role.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: Classification by utility's corporate standards and practices.

DerivedEntities.Name: CRROrgRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Identifies a way in which an organisation may participate with a defined Congestion Revenue Right (CRR).

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of role the organisation is with regards to the congestion revenue rights.

Attributes.Name: status
Attributes.Description: Status of congestion revenue rights organisation role.

DerivedEntities.Name: Customer
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation receiving services from service supplier.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of customer.

Attributes.Name: locale
Attributes.Description: Locale designating language to use in communications with this customer.

Attributes.Name: priority
Attributes.Description: Priority of the customer.

Attributes.Name: pucNumber
Attributes.Description: (if applicable) Public utilities commission (PUC) identification number.

Attributes.Name: specialNeed
Attributes.Description: True if customer organisation has special service needs such as life support, hospitals, etc.

Attributes.Name: status
Attributes.Description: Status of this customer.

Attributes.Name: vip
Attributes.Description: (deprecated) (use 'priority' instead) True if this is an important customer. Importance is for matters different than those in 'specialNeed' attribute.

DerivedEntities.Name: DocumentOrganisationRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Role an organisation plays with respect to documents.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnvironmentalDataAuthority
DerivedEntities.Description: An entity defining classifications or categories of environmental information, like phenomena or alerts.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnvironmentalDataProvider
DerivedEntities.Description: Entity providing environmental data.  Could be an observed weather data provider, an entity providing forecasts, an authority providing alerts, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: Manufacturer
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that manufactures asset products.

DerivedEntities.Name: MarketRole
DerivedEntities.Description: The external intended behavior played by a party within the electricity market.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: The kind of market roles that can be played by parties for given domains within the electricity market. Types are flexible using dataType of string for free-entry of role types.

DerivedEntities.Name: OrgOrgRole
DerivedEntities.Description:
Roles played between Organisations and other Organisations. This includes role ups for ogranisations, cost centers, profit centers, regulatory reporting, etc.
Note that the parent and child relationship is indicated by the name on each end of the association.

Attributes.Name: clientID
Attributes.Description: Identifiers of the organisation held by another organisation, such as a government agency (federal, state, province, city, county), financial institution (Dun and Bradstreet), etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: PersonOrganisationRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Role an organisation plays with respect to persons.

Attributes.Name: clientID
Attributes.Description: Identifiers of the person held by an organisation, such as a government agency (federal, state, province, city, county), financial institutions, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: PropertyOrganisationRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Role an organisation plays with respect to property (for example, the organisation may be the owner, renter, occupier, taxiing authority, etc.).

DerivedEntities.Name: ServiceSupplier
DerivedEntities.Description: Organisation that provides services to customers.

Attributes.Name: issuerIdentificationNumber
Attributes.Description: Unique transaction reference prefix number issued to an entity by the International Organization for Standardization for the purpose of tagging onto electronic financial transactions, as defined in ISO/IEC 7812-1 and ISO/IEC 7812-2.

Attributes.Name: kind
Attributes.Description: Kind of supplier.

DerivedEntities.Name: OrgPnodeAllocation
DerivedEntities.Description: This class models the allocation between asset owners and pricing nodes.

Attributes.Name: maxMWAllocation
Attributes.Description: Maximum MW for the Source/Sink for the Allocation

DerivedEntities.Name: OrgResOwnership
DerivedEntities.Description: This class model the ownership percent and type of ownership between resource and organisation.

Attributes.Name: asscType
Attributes.Description: association type for the association between Organisation and Resource:

Attributes.Name: masterSchedulingCoordinatorFlag
Attributes.Description: Flag to indicate that the SC representing the Resource is the Master SC.

Attributes.Name: ownershipPercent
Attributes.Description: ownership percentage for each resource

DerivedEntities.Name: Ownership
DerivedEntities.Description: Ownership of e.g. asset.

Attributes.Name: share
Attributes.Description: Share of this ownership.

DerivedEntities.Name: Participation
DerivedEntities.Description: Participation level of a given Pnode in a given AggregatePnode.

Attributes.Name: factor
Attributes.Description: Used to calculate "participation" of Pnode in an AggregatePnode. For example, for regulation region this factor is 1 and total sum of all factors for a specific regulation region does not have to be 1. For pricing zone the total sum of all factors has to be 1.

DerivedEntities.Name: PerLengthLineParameter
DerivedEntities.Description: Common type for per-length electrical catalogues describing line parameters.

DerivedEntities.Name: PerLengthDCLineParameter
DerivedEntities.Description: Common type for per-length electrical catalogues describing DC line parameters.

Attributes.Name: capacitance
Attributes.Description: Capacitance per unit of length of the DC line segment; significant for cables only.

Attributes.Name: inductance
Attributes.Description: Inductance per unit of length of the DC line segment.

Attributes.Name: resistance
Attributes.Description: Resistance per length of the DC line segment.

DerivedEntities.Name: PerLengthImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description: Common type for per-length impedance electrical catalogues.

DerivedEntities.Name: PerLengthPhaseImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description: Impedance and admittance parameters per unit length for n-wire unbalanced lines, in matrix form.

Attributes.Name: conductorCount
Attributes.Description: Number of phase, neutral, and other wires retained. Constrains the number of matrix elements and the phase codes that can be used with this matrix.

DerivedEntities.Name: PerLengthSequenceImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description: Sequence impedance and admittance parameters per unit length, for transposed lines of 1, 2, or 3 phases. For 1-phase lines, define x=x0=xself. For 2-phase lines, define x=xs-xm and x0=xs+xm.

Attributes.Name: b0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: bch
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: g0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: gch
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence series resistance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series resistance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence series reactance, per unit of length.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series reactance, per unit of length.

DerivedEntities.Name: Person
DerivedEntities.Description: General purpose information for name and other information to contact people.

DerivedEntities.Name: OldPerson
DerivedEntities.Description: General purpose information for name and other information to contact people.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description:
Utility-specific classification for this person, according to the utility's corporate standards and practices. Examples include employee, contractor, agent, not affiliated, etc.
Note that this field is not used to indicate whether this person is a customer of the utility. Often an employee or contractor is also a customer. Customer information is gained with relationship to Organisation and CustomerData. In similar fashion, this field does not indicate the various roles this person may fill as part of utility operations.

Attributes.Name: electronicAddress
Attributes.Description: Electronic address.

Attributes.Name: firstName
Attributes.Description: Person's first name.

Attributes.Name: landlinePhone
Attributes.Description: Landline phone number.

Attributes.Name: lastName
Attributes.Description: Person's last (family, sir) name.

Attributes.Name: mName
Attributes.Description: Middle name(s) or initial(s).

Attributes.Name: mobilePhone
Attributes.Description: Mobile phone number.

Attributes.Name: prefix
Attributes.Description: A prefix or title for the person's name, such as Miss, Mister, Doctor, etc.

Attributes.Name: specialNeed
Attributes.Description: Special service needs for the person (contact) are described; examples include life support, etc.

Attributes.Name: suffix
Attributes.Description: A suffix for the person's name, such as II, III, etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: DocumentPersonRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Person role with respect to documents.

DerivedEntities.Name: Approver
DerivedEntities.Description: Person who accepted/signed or rejected the document.

DerivedEntities.Name: Author
DerivedEntities.Description: Person who created document or activity record.

DerivedEntities.Name: Editor
DerivedEntities.Description: Person who modified the document.

DerivedEntities.Name: Issuer
DerivedEntities.Description: Person who issued the document and is responsible for its content.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperationPersonRole
DerivedEntities.Description: Person role in the context of utility operations.

DerivedEntities.Name: CrewMember
DerivedEntities.Description: Member of a crew.

DerivedEntities.Name: FieldSafetySupervisor
DerivedEntities.Description: Crew member on work site responsible for all local safety measures for the work crew doing maintenance, construction and repair in a substation or on a power line/cable.

DerivedEntities.Name: Operator
DerivedEntities.Description: Control room operator.

DerivedEntities.Name: OperationsSafetySupervisor
DerivedEntities.Description: Operator with responsibility that the work in high voltage installation is executed in a safe manner and according to safety regulation.

DerivedEntities.Name: PhaseTapChangerTable
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes a tabular curve for how the phase angle difference and impedance varies with the tap step.

DerivedEntities.Name: PhenomenonClassification
DerivedEntities.Description: A pre-defined phenomenon classification as defined by a particular authority.

DerivedEntities.Name: PlannedMarketEvent
DerivedEntities.Description: This class represents planned events. Used to model the various planned events in a market (closing time, clearing time, etc.)

Attributes.Name: plannedTime
Attributes.Description: This is relative time so that this attribute can be used by more than one planned market. For example the bid submission is 10am everyday.

Attributes.Name: eventType
Attributes.Description: Planned event type.

DerivedEntities.Name: Pnode
DerivedEntities.Description: A pricing node is directly associated with a connectivity node.  It is a pricing location for which market participants submit their bids, offers, buy/sell CRRs, and settle.

DerivedEntities.Name: AggregatedPnode
DerivedEntities.Description: An aggregated pricing node is a specialized type of pricing node used to model items such as System Zone, Default Price Zone, Custom Price Zone, Control Area, Aggregated Generation, Aggregated Particpating Load, Aggregated Non-Participating Load, Trading Hub, Designated Control Area(DCA) Zone.

DerivedEntities.Name: CongestionArea
DerivedEntities.Description: Designated Congestion Area Definition (DCA).

Attributes.Name: apnodeType
Attributes.Description: Aggregate Price Node Types

Attributes.Name: participationCategory
Attributes.Description:
Designated Control Area participation in LMP price measurement

'Y' - Participates in both Local Market Power Mitigation (LMPM) and System Market Power Mitigation (SMPM)
'N' - Not included in LMP price measures
'S' - Participatesin SMPM price measures
'L' - Participatesin LMPM price measures

DerivedEntities.Name: IndividualPnode
DerivedEntities.Description: Individual pricing node based on Pnode.

Attributes.Name: isPublic
Attributes.Description: If true, this Pnode is public (prices are published for DA/RT and FTR markets), otherwise it is private (location is not usable by market for bidding/FTRs/transactions).

DerivedEntities.Name: PointOfSale
DerivedEntities.Description: Logical point where transactions take place with operational interaction between cashier and the payment system; in certain cases the point of sale interacts directly with the end customer, in which case the cashier might not be a real person: for example a self-service kiosk or over the internet.

Attributes.Name: location
Attributes.Description: Local description for where this point of sale is physically located.

DerivedEntities.Name: PowerSystemResource
DerivedEntities.Description: A power system resource (PSR) can be an item of equipment such as a switch, an equipment container containing many individual items of equipment such as a substation, or an organisational entity such as sub-control area. Power system resources can have measurements associated.

DerivedEntities.Name: ACLineSegmentPhase
DerivedEntities.Description: Represents a single wire of an alternating current line segment.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The phase connection of the wire at both ends.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: Number designation for this line segment phase. Each line segment phase within a line segment should have a unique sequence number. This is useful for unbalanced modelling to bind the mathematical model (PhaseImpedanceData of PerLengthPhaseImpedance) with the connectivity model (this class) and the physical model (WirePosition) without tight coupling.

DerivedEntities.Name: AirCompressor
DerivedEntities.Description: Combustion turbine air compressor which is an integral part of a compressed air energy storage (CAES) plant.

Attributes.Name: airCompressorRating
Attributes.Description: Rating of the CAES air compressor.

DerivedEntities.Name: CAESPlant
DerivedEntities.Description: Compressed air energy storage plant.

Attributes.Name: energyStorageCapacity
Attributes.Description: The rated energy storage capacity. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: ratedCapacityP
Attributes.Description: The CAES plant's gross rated generating capacity. The attribute shall be a positive value.

DerivedEntities.Name: CogenerationPlant
DerivedEntities.Description: A set of thermal generating units for the production of electrical energy and process steam (usually from the output of the steam turbines). The steam sendout is typically used for industrial purposes or for municipal heating and cooling.

Attributes.Name: cogenHPSendoutRating
Attributes.Description: The high pressure steam sendout.

Attributes.Name: cogenLPSendoutRating
Attributes.Description: The low pressure steam sendout.

Attributes.Name: ratedP
Attributes.Description:
The rated output active power of the cogeneration plant.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: cogenHPSteamRating
Attributes.Description: The high pressure steam rating.

Attributes.Name: cogenLPSteamRating
Attributes.Description: The low pressure steam rating.

DerivedEntities.Name: CombinedCyclePlant
DerivedEntities.Description: A set of combustion turbines and steam turbines where the exhaust heat from the combustion turbines is recovered to make steam for the steam turbines, resulting in greater overall plant efficiency.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktCombinedCyclePlant
DerivedEntities.Description:
Subclass of Production: CombinedCyclePlant from IEC 61970 package.
A set of combustion turbines and steam turbines where the exhaust heat from the combustion turbines is recovered to make steam for the steam turbines, resulting in greater overall plant efficiency.

Attributes.Name: combCyclePlantRating
Attributes.Description: The combined cycle plant's active power output rating.

DerivedEntities.Name: CommunicationLink
DerivedEntities.Description: The connection to remote units is through one or more communication links. Reduntant links may exist. The CommunicationLink class inherits PowerSystemResource. The intention is to allow CommunicationLinks to have Measurements. These Measurements can be used to model link status as operational, out of service, unit failure etc.

DerivedEntities.Name: IPAccessPoint
DerivedEntities.Description: Internet Protocol Access Point – used to represent an addressing structure is based upon an Internet Protocol (IP) address.

DerivedEntities.Name: TCPAccessPoint
DerivedEntities.Description: Allows addressing and behavioural information regarding the use of TCP by ICCP links.

DerivedEntities.Name: ISOUpperLayer
DerivedEntities.Description: Is a set of configure addressing information that is required since ICCP utilizes addressing other than a TCP port.

Attributes.Name: aeQual
Attributes.Description: Is the AE qualifier and represents further application level addressing information.

Attributes.Name: apTitle
Attributes.Description: Is a sequence of integer strings separated by ".".  The value, in conjunction with other application addressing attributes (e.g. other APs) are used to select a specific application (e.g. the ICCP application entity) per the OSI reference model.  The sequence, and its values, represent a namespace whose values are governed by ISO/IEC 7498-3.

Attributes.Name: osiSsel
Attributes.Description: Is the OSI session layer addressing information.

Attributes.Name: osiTsel
Attributes.Description: Is the OSI Transport Layer addressing information.

Attributes.Name: aeInvoke
Attributes.Description: Is part of the Application Entity addressing as specified by ISO Addressing.

Attributes.Name: apInvoke
Attributes.Description: Is a further application level OSI addressing parameter.

Attributes.Name: osiPsel
Attributes.Description: Is the addressing selector for OSI presentation addressing.

Attributes.Name: keepAliveTime
Attributes.Description: Indicates the default interval at which TCP will check if the TCP connection is still valid.

Attributes.Name: port
Attributes.Description:
This value is only needed to be specified for called nodes (e.g. those that respond to a TCP.Open request).

This value specifies the TCP port to be used. Well known and "registered" ports are preferred and can be found at:
 http://www.iana.org/assignments/service-names-port-numbers/service-names-port-numbers.xhtml

For IEC 60870-6 TASE.2 (e.g. ICCP) and IEC 61850, the value used shall be 102 for non-TLS protected exchanges. The value shall be 3782 for TLS transported ICCP and 61850 exchanges.

Attributes.Name: address
Attributes.Description: Is the dotted decimal IP Address resolve the IP address. The format is controlled by the value of the addressType.

Attributes.Name: gateway
Attributes.Description: Is the dotted decimal IPAddress of the first hop router.  Format is controlled by the addressType.

Attributes.Name: addressType
Attributes.Description: IP address type.

Attributes.Name: subnet
Attributes.Description: This is the IP subnet mask which controls the local vs non-local routing.

DerivedEntities.Name: ConnectivityNodeContainer
DerivedEntities.Description: A base class for all objects that may contain connectivity nodes or topological nodes.

DerivedEntities.Name: EquipmentContainer
DerivedEntities.Description: A modelling construct to provide a root class for containing equipment.

DerivedEntities.Name: Bay
DerivedEntities.Description: A collection of power system resources (within a given substation) including conducting equipment, protection relays, measurements, and telemetry.  A bay typically represents a physical grouping related to modularization of equipment.

Attributes.Name: bayEnergyMeasFlag
Attributes.Description: Indicates the presence/absence of energy measurements.

Attributes.Name: bayPowerMeasFlag
Attributes.Description: Indicates the presence/absence of active/reactive power measurements.

Attributes.Name: breakerConfiguration
Attributes.Description: Breaker configuration.

Attributes.Name: busBarConfiguration
Attributes.Description: Busbar configuration.

DerivedEntities.Name: DCEquipmentContainer
DerivedEntities.Description: A modelling construct to provide a root class for containment of DC as well as AC equipment. The class differ from the EquipmentContaner for AC in that it may also contain DCNode-s. Hence it can contain both AC and DC equipment.

DerivedEntities.Name: DCConverterUnit
DerivedEntities.Description: Indivisible operative unit comprising all equipment between the point of common coupling on the AC side and the point of common coupling – DC side, essentially one or more converters, together with one or more converter transformers, converter control equipment, essential protective and switching devices and auxiliaries, if any, used for conversion.

Attributes.Name: operationMode
Attributes.Description: The operating mode of an HVDC bipole (bipolar, monopolar metallic return, etc).

DerivedEntities.Name: DCLine
DerivedEntities.Description: Overhead lines and/or cables connecting two or more HVDC substations.

DerivedEntities.Name: Feeder
DerivedEntities.Description:
A collection of equipment for organizational purposes, used for grouping distribution resources.
The organization a feeder does not necessarily reflect connectivity or current operation state.

DerivedEntities.Name: Line
DerivedEntities.Description: Contains equipment beyond a substation belonging to a power transmission line.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktLine
DerivedEntities.Description: Subclass for IEC61970:Wires:Line.

DerivedEntities.Name: Plant
DerivedEntities.Description: A Plant is a collection of equipment for purposes of generation.

DerivedEntities.Name: Substation
DerivedEntities.Description: A collection of equipment for purposes other than generation or utilization, through which electric energy in bulk is passed for the purposes of switching or modifying its characteristics.

DerivedEntities.Name: VoltageLevel
DerivedEntities.Description: A collection of equipment at one common system voltage forming a switchgear. The equipment typically consists of breakers, busbars, instrumentation, control, regulation and protection devices as well as assemblies of all these.

Attributes.Name: highVoltageLimit
Attributes.Description:
The bus bar's high voltage limit.
The limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with lowVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present.

Attributes.Name: lowVoltageLimit
Attributes.Description:
The bus bar's low voltage limit.
The limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with highVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present.

DerivedEntities.Name: EquivalentNetwork
DerivedEntities.Description: A class that groups electrical equivalents, including internal nodes, of a network that has been reduced. The ConnectivityNodes contained in the equivalent are intended to reflect internal nodes of the equivalent. The boundary Connectivity nodes where the equivalent connects outside itself are not contained by the equivalent.

DerivedEntities.Name: ControlArea
DerivedEntities.Description:
A control area is a grouping of generating units and/or loads and a cutset of tie lines (as terminals) which may be used for a variety of purposes including automatic generation control, power flow solution area interchange control specification, and input to load forecasting. All generation and load within the area defined by the terminals on the border are considered in the area interchange control. Note that any number of overlapping control area specifications can be superimposed on the physical model. The following general principles apply to ControlArea:
1.  The control area orientation for net interchange is positive for an import, negative for an export.
2.  The control area net interchange is determined by summing flows in Terminals. The Terminals are identified by creating a set of TieFlow objects associated with a ControlArea object. Each TieFlow object identifies one Terminal.
3.  In a single network model, a tie between two control areas must be modelled in both control area specifications, such that the two representations of the tie flow sum to zero.
4.  The normal orientation of Terminal flow is positive for flow into the conducting equipment that owns the Terminal. (i.e. flow from a bus into a device is positive.) However, the orientation of each flow in the control area specification must align with the control area convention, i.e. import is positive. If the orientation of the Terminal flow referenced by a TieFlow is positive into the control area, then this is confirmed by setting TieFlow.positiveFlowIn flag TRUE. If not, the orientation must be reversed by setting the TieFlow.positiveFlowIn flag FALSE.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktControlArea
DerivedEntities.Description: Market subclass of IEC 61970:ControlArea.

Attributes.Name: netInterchange
Attributes.Description: The specified positive net interchange into the control area, i.e. positive sign means flow into the area.

Attributes.Name: pTolerance
Attributes.Description: Active power net interchange tolerance. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: The primary type of control area definition used to determine if this is used for automatic generation control, for planning interchange control, or other purposes.   A control area specified with primary type of automatic generation control could still be forecast and used as an interchange area in power flow analysis.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnergyConsumerPhase
DerivedEntities.Description: A single phase of an energy consumer.

Attributes.Name: pfixed
Attributes.Description: Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: Phase of this energy consumer component.   If the energy consumer is wye connected, the connection is from the indicated phase to the central ground or neutral point.  If the energy consumer is delta connected, the phase indicates an energy consumer connected from the indicated phase to the next logical non-neutral phase.

Attributes.Name: qfixed
Attributes.Description: Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: qfixedPct
Attributes.Description: Fixed reactive power as per cent of load group fixed reactive power. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: p
Attributes.Description:
Active power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

Attributes.Name: pfixedPct
Attributes.Description: Fixed active power as per cent of load group fixed active power. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: q
Attributes.Description:
Reactive power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnergySourcePhase
DerivedEntities.Description: Represents the single phase information of an unbalanced energy source.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: Phase of this energy source component.   If the energy source wye connected, the connection is from the indicated phase to the central ground or neutral point.  If the energy source is delta connected, the phase indicates an energy source connected from the indicated phase to the next logical non-neutral phase.

DerivedEntities.Name: Equipment
DerivedEntities.Description: The parts of a power system that are physical devices, electronic or mechanical.

DerivedEntities.Name: AuxiliaryEquipment
DerivedEntities.Description:
AuxiliaryEquipment describe equipment that is not performing any primary functions but support for the equipment performing the primary function.
AuxiliaryEquipment is attached to primary equipment via an association with Terminal.

DerivedEntities.Name: FaultIndicator
DerivedEntities.Description: A FaultIndicator is typically only an indicator (which may or may not be remotely monitored), and not a piece of equipment that actually initiates a protection event. It is used for FLISR (Fault Location, Isolation and Restoration) purposes, assisting with the dispatch of crews to "most likely" part of the network (i.e. assists with determining circuit section where the fault most likely happened).

DerivedEntities.Name: Sensor
DerivedEntities.Description: This class describe devices that transform a measured quantity into signals that can be presented at displays, used in control or be recorded.

DerivedEntities.Name: CurrentTransformer
DerivedEntities.Description: Instrument transformer used to measure electrical qualities of the circuit that is being protected and/or monitored. Typically used as current transducer for the purpose of metering or protection. A typical secondary current rating would be 5A.

Attributes.Name: accuracyClass
Attributes.Description: CT accuracy classification.

Attributes.Name: coreBurden
Attributes.Description: Power burden of the CT core.

Attributes.Name: usage
Attributes.Description: Intended usage of the CT; i.e. metering, protection.

Attributes.Name: accuracyLimit
Attributes.Description: Percent of rated current for which the CT remains accurate within specified limits.

Attributes.Name: ctClass
Attributes.Description: CT classification; i.e. class 10P.

DerivedEntities.Name: PostLineSensor
DerivedEntities.Description: A sensor used mainly in overhead distribution networks as the source of both current and voltage measurements.

DerivedEntities.Name: PotentialTransformer
DerivedEntities.Description: Instrument transformer (also known as Voltage Transformer) used to measure electrical qualities of the circuit that is being protected and/or monitored. Typically used as voltage transducer for the purpose of metering, protection, or sometimes auxiliary substation supply. A typical secondary voltage rating would be 120V.

Attributes.Name: accuracyClass
Attributes.Description: PT accuracy classification.

Attributes.Name: nominalRatio
Attributes.Description: Nominal ratio between the primary and secondary voltage.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: Potential transformer construction type.

Attributes.Name: ptClass
Attributes.Description: Potential transformer (PT) classification covering burden.

DerivedEntities.Name: SurgeArrester
DerivedEntities.Description: Shunt device, installed on the network, usually in the proximity of electrical equipment in order to protect the said equipment against transient voltage transients caused by lightning or switching activity.

DerivedEntities.Name: WaveTrap
DerivedEntities.Description: Line traps are devices that impede high frequency power line carrier signals yet present a negligible impedance at the main power frequency.

DerivedEntities.Name: CompositeSwitch
DerivedEntities.Description:
A model of a set of individual Switches normally enclosed within the same cabinet and possibly with interlocks that restrict the combination of switch positions. These are typically found in medium voltage distribution networks. 
A CompositeSwitch could represent a Ring-Main-Unit (RMU), or pad-mounted switchgear, with primitive internal devices such as an internal bus-bar plus 3 or 4 internal switches each of which may individually be open or closed. A CompositeSwitch and a set of contained Switches can also be used to represent a multi-position switch e.g. a switch that can connect a circuit to Ground, Open or Busbar.

Attributes.Name: compositeSwitchType
Attributes.Description: An alphanumeric code that can be used as a reference to extra information such as the description of the interlocking scheme if any.

DerivedEntities.Name: ConductingEquipment
DerivedEntities.Description: The parts of the AC power system that are designed to carry current or that are conductively connected through terminals.

DerivedEntities.Name: ACDCConverter
DerivedEntities.Description: A unit with valves for three phases, together with unit control equipment, essential protective and switching devices, DC storage capacitors, phase reactors and auxiliaries, if any, used for conversion.

DerivedEntities.Name: CsConverter
DerivedEntities.Description:
DC side of the current source converter (CSC).
The firing angle controls the dc voltage at the converter, both for rectifier and inverter. The difference between the dc voltages of the rectifier and inverter determines the dc current. The extinction angle is used to limit the dc voltage at the inverter, if needed, and is not used in active power control. The firing angle, transformer tap position and number of connected filters are the primary means to control a current source dc line. Higher level controls are built on top, e.g. dc voltage, dc current and active power. From a steady state perspective it is sufficient to specify the wanted active power transfer (ACDCConverter.targetPpcc) and the control functions will set the dc voltage, dc current, firing angle, transformer tap position and number of connected filters to meet this. Therefore attributes targetAlpha and targetGamma are not applicable in this case.
The reactive power consumed by the converter is a function of the firing angle, transformer tap position and number of connected filter, which can be approximated with half of the active power. The losses is a function of the dc voltage and dc current.
The attributes minAlpha and maxAlpha define the range of firing angles for rectifier operation between which no discrete tap changer action takes place. The range is typically 10-18 degrees.
The attributes minGamma and maxGamma define the range of extinction angles for inverter operation between which no discrete tap changer action takes place. The range is typically 17-20 degrees.

Attributes.Name: alpha
Attributes.Description: Firing angle that determines the dc voltage at the converter dc terminal. Typical value between 10 degrees and 18 degrees for a rectifier. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxAlpha
Attributes.Description: Maximum firing angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: minAlpha
Attributes.Description: Minimum firing angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: minIdc
Attributes.Description: The minimum direct current (Id) on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: pPccControl
Attributes.Description: Kind of active power control.

Attributes.Name: targetAlpha
Attributes.Description: Target firing angle. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. It is only applicable for rectifier if continuous tap changer control is used. Allowed values are within the range minAlpha<=targetAlpha<=maxAlpha. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: targetGamma
Attributes.Description: Target extinction angle. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. It is only applicable for inverter if continuous tap changer control is used. Allowed values are within the range minGamma<=targetGamma<=maxGamma. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: gamma
Attributes.Description: Extinction angle. It is used to limit the dc voltage at the inverter if needed. Typical value between 17 degrees and 20 degrees for an inverter. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxGamma
Attributes.Description: Maximum extinction angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxIdc
Attributes.Description: The maximum direct current (Id) on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data use in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: minGamma
Attributes.Description: Minimum extinction angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: operatingMode
Attributes.Description: Indicates whether the DC pole is operating as an inverter or as a rectifier. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow.

Attributes.Name: ratedIdc
Attributes.Description: Rated converter DC current, also called IdN. The attribute shall be a positive value. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow.

Attributes.Name: targetIdc
Attributes.Description: DC current target value. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

DerivedEntities.Name: VsConverter
DerivedEntities.Description: DC side of the voltage source converter (VSC).

Attributes.Name: delta
Attributes.Description: Angle between VsConverter.uv and ACDCConverter.uc. It is converter’s state variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: droop
Attributes.Description: Droop constant. The pu value is obtained as D [kV/MW] x Sb / Ubdc. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxModulationIndex
Attributes.Description: The maximum quotient between the AC converter voltage (Uc) and DC voltage (Ud). A factor typically less than 1. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow.

Attributes.Name: pPccControl
Attributes.Description: Kind of control of real power and/or DC voltage.

Attributes.Name: qShare
Attributes.Description: Reactive power sharing factor among parallel converters on Uac control. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: targetPowerFactorPcc
Attributes.Description: Power factor target at the AC side, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: targetUpcc
Attributes.Description: Voltage target in AC grid, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: droopCompensation
Attributes.Description: Compensation constant. Used to compensate for voltage drop when controlling voltage at a distant bus. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxValveCurrent
Attributes.Description: The maximum current through a valve. It is converter’s configuration data.

Attributes.Name: qPccControl
Attributes.Description: Kind of reactive power control.

Attributes.Name: targetPhasePcc
Attributes.Description: Phase target at AC side, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: targetPWMfactor
Attributes.Description: Magnitude of pulse-modulation factor. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: targetQpcc
Attributes.Description: Reactive power injection target in AC grid, at point of common coupling.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: uv
Attributes.Description: Line-to-line voltage on the valve side of the converter transformer. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: baseS
Attributes.Description: Base apparent power of the converter pole. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: idc
Attributes.Description: Converter DC current, also called Id. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow.

Attributes.Name: idleLoss
Attributes.Description: Active power loss in pole at no power transfer. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: maxP
Attributes.Description: Maximum active power limit. The value is overwritten by values of VsCapabilityCurve, if present.

Attributes.Name: maxUdc
Attributes.Description: The maximum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: minP
Attributes.Description: Minimum active power limit. The value is overwritten by values of VsCapabilityCurve, if present.

Attributes.Name: minUdc
Attributes.Description: The minimum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: numberOfValves
Attributes.Description: Number of valves in the converter. Used in loss calculations.

Attributes.Name: p
Attributes.Description:
Active power at the point of common coupling. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution in the case a simplified power flow model is used.

Attributes.Name: poleLossP
Attributes.Description:
The active power loss at a DC Pole 
= idleLoss + switchingLoss*|Idc| + resitiveLoss*Idc^2.
For lossless operation Pdc=Pac.
For rectifier operation with losses Pdc=Pac-lossP.
For inverter operation with losses Pdc=Pac+lossP.
It is converter’s state variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: q
Attributes.Description:
Reactive power at the point of common coupling. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution in the case a simplified power flow model is used.

Attributes.Name: ratedUdc
Attributes.Description: Rated converter DC voltage, also called UdN. The attribute shall be a positive value. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. For instance a bipolar HVDC link with value  200 kV has a 400kV difference between the dc lines.

Attributes.Name: resistiveLoss
Attributes.Description: It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. Refer to poleLossP. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: switchingLoss
Attributes.Description: Switching losses, relative to the base apparent power 'baseS'. Refer to poleLossP. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: targetPpcc
Attributes.Description: Real power injection target in AC grid, at point of common coupling.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: targetUdc
Attributes.Description: Target value for DC voltage magnitude. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: uc
Attributes.Description: Line-to-line converter voltage, the voltage at the AC side of the valve. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: udc
Attributes.Description: Converter voltage at the DC side, also called Ud. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: valveU0
Attributes.Description: Valve threshold voltage, also called Uvalve. Forward voltage drop when the valve is conducting. Used in loss calculations, i.e. the switchLoss depend on numberOfValves * valveU0.

DerivedEntities.Name: Clamp
DerivedEntities.Description:
A Clamp is a galvanic connection at a line segment where other equipment is connected. A Clamp does not cut the line segment. 
A Clamp is ConductingEquipment and has one Terminal with an associated ConnectivityNode. Any other ConductingEquipment can be connected to the Clamp ConnectivityNode.

Attributes.Name: lengthFromTerminal1
Attributes.Description: The length to the place where the clamp is located starting from side one of the line segment, i.e. the line segment terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

DerivedEntities.Name: Conductor
DerivedEntities.Description: Combination of conducting material with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry current between points in the power system.

DerivedEntities.Name: ACLineSegment
DerivedEntities.Description:
A wire or combination of wires, with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry alternating current between points in the power system.
For symmetrical, transposed three phase lines, it is sufficient to use attributes of the line segment, which describe impedances and admittances for the entire length of the segment.  Additionally impedances can be computed by using length and associated per length impedances.
The BaseVoltage at the two ends of ACLineSegments in a Line shall have the same BaseVoltage.nominalVoltage. However, boundary lines may have slightly different BaseVoltage.nominalVoltages and variation is allowed. Larger voltage difference in general requires use of an equivalent branch.

DerivedEntities.Name: MktACLineSegment
DerivedEntities.Description: Subclass of IEC 61970:Wires:ACLineSegment.

Attributes.Name: bch
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.  This value represents the full charging over the full length of the line.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: shortCircuitEndTemperature
Attributes.Description: Maximum permitted temperature at the end of SC for the calculation of minimum short-circuit currents. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: b0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: g0ch
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: gch
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

DerivedEntities.Name: WireSegment
DerivedEntities.Description: A two terminal and power conducting device of negligible impedance and length represented as zero impedance device that can be used to connect auxiliary equipment to its terminals.

Attributes.Name: length
Attributes.Description: Segment length for calculating line section capabilities.

DerivedEntities.Name: Connector
DerivedEntities.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation and are modelled with a single logical terminal.

DerivedEntities.Name: BusbarSection
DerivedEntities.Description:
A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation. 
Voltage measurements are typically obtained from voltage transformers that are connected to busbar sections. A bus bar section may have many physical terminals but for analysis is modelled with exactly one logical terminal.

Attributes.Name: ipMax
Attributes.Description:
Maximum allowable peak short-circuit current of busbar (Ipmax in IEC 60909-0). 
Mechanical limit of the busbar in the substation itself. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

DerivedEntities.Name: Junction
DerivedEntities.Description: A point where one or more conducting equipments are connected with zero resistance.

DerivedEntities.Name: EarthFaultCompensator
DerivedEntities.Description: A conducting equipment used to represent a connection to ground which is typically used to compensate earth faults.   An earth fault compensator device modelled with a single terminal implies a second terminal solidly connected to ground.  If two terminals are modelled, the ground is not assumed and normal connection rules apply.

DerivedEntities.Name: GroundingImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description: A fixed impedance device used for grounding.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Reactance of device.

DerivedEntities.Name: PetersenCoil
DerivedEntities.Description: A variable impedance device normally used to offset line charging during single line faults in an ungrounded section of network.

Attributes.Name: mode
Attributes.Description: The mode of operation of the Petersen coil.

Attributes.Name: offsetCurrent
Attributes.Description: The offset current that the Petersen coil controller is operating from the resonant point.  This is normally a fixed amount for which the controller is configured and could be positive or negative.  Typically 0 to 60 A depending on voltage and resonance conditions.

Attributes.Name: xGroundMax
Attributes.Description: The maximum reactance.

Attributes.Name: xGroundNominal
Attributes.Description: The nominal reactance.  This is the operating point (normally over compensation) that is defined based on the resonance point in the healthy network condition.  The impedance is calculated based on nominal voltage divided by position current.

Attributes.Name: nominalU
Attributes.Description: The nominal voltage for which the coil is designed.

Attributes.Name: positionCurrent
Attributes.Description: The control current used to control the Petersen coil also known as the position current.  Typically in the range of 20 mA to 200 mA.

Attributes.Name: xGroundMin
Attributes.Description: The minimum reactance.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Nominal resistance of device.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnergyConnection
DerivedEntities.Description: A connection of energy generation or consumption on the power system model.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnergyConsumer
DerivedEntities.Description:
Generic user of energy - a  point of consumption on the power system model.
EnergyConsumer.pfixed, .qfixed, .pfixedPct and .qfixedPct have meaning only if there is no LoadResponseCharacteristic associated with EnergyConsumer or if LoadResponseCharacteristic.exponentModel is set to False.

DerivedEntities.Name: ConformLoad
DerivedEntities.Description: ConformLoad represent loads that follow a daily load change pattern where the pattern can be used to scale the load with a system load.

DerivedEntities.Name: NonConformLoad
DerivedEntities.Description: NonConformLoad represents loads that do not follow a daily load change pattern and whose changes are not correlated with the daily load change pattern.

DerivedEntities.Name: StationSupply
DerivedEntities.Description: Station supply with load derived from the station output.

Attributes.Name: customerCount
Attributes.Description: Number of individual customers represented by this demand.

Attributes.Name: p
Attributes.Description:
Active power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

Attributes.Name: pfixedPct
Attributes.Description: Fixed active power as a percentage of load group fixed active power. Used to represent the time-varying components.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: q
Attributes.Description:
Reactive power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

Attributes.Name: qfixedPct
Attributes.Description: Fixed reactive power as a percentage of load group fixed reactive power. Used to represent the time-varying components.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: grounded
Attributes.Description: Used for Yn and Zn connections. True if the neutral is solidly grounded.

Attributes.Name: pfixed
Attributes.Description: Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity and does not vary as load group value varies. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

Attributes.Name: phaseConnection
Attributes.Description: The type of phase connection, such as wye or delta.

Attributes.Name: qfixed
Attributes.Description: Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity and does not vary as load group value varies. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

DerivedEntities.Name: EnergySource
DerivedEntities.Description: A generic equivalent for an energy supplier on a transmission or distribution voltage level.

Attributes.Name: activePower
Attributes.Description:
High voltage source active injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

Attributes.Name: pMin
Attributes.Description: This is the minimum active power that can be produced by the source. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence Thevenin resistance.

Attributes.Name: rn
Attributes.Description: Negative sequence Thevenin resistance.

Attributes.Name: voltageMagnitude
Attributes.Description: Phase-to-phase open circuit voltage magnitude used when voltage characteristics need to be imposed at the node associated with the terminal of the energy source, such as when voltages and angles from the transmission level are used as input to the distribution network. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence Thevenin reactance.

Attributes.Name: nominalVoltage
Attributes.Description: Phase-to-phase nominal voltage.

Attributes.Name: pMax
Attributes.Description: This is the maximum active power that can be produced by the source. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence Thevenin resistance.

Attributes.Name: reactivePower
Attributes.Description:
High voltage source reactive injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

Attributes.Name: voltageAngle
Attributes.Description: Phase angle of a-phase open circuit used when voltage characteristics need to be imposed at the node associated with the terminal of the energy source, such as when voltages and angles from the transmission level are used as input to the distribution network. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence Thevenin reactance.

Attributes.Name: xn
Attributes.Description: Negative sequence Thevenin reactance.

DerivedEntities.Name: RegulatingCondEq
DerivedEntities.Description: A type of conducting equipment that can regulate a quantity (i.e. voltage or flow) at a specific point in the network.

DerivedEntities.Name: ExternalNetworkInjection

Attributes.Name: aVRDelay
Attributes.Description: An automatic voltage regulation delay (AVRDelay) which is the time delay from a change in voltage to when the capacitor is allowed to change state. This filters out temporary changes in voltage.

Attributes.Name: grounded

Attributes.Name: maximumSections

Attributes.Name: normalSections
Attributes.Description: The normal number of sections switched in. The value shall be between zero and ShuntCompensator.maximumSections.

Attributes.Name: sections
Attributes.Description:
Shunt compensator sections in use. Starting value for steady state solution. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. Non integer values are allowed to support continuous variables. The reasons for continuous value are to support study cases where no discrete shunt compensators has yet been designed, a solutions where a narrow voltage band force the sections to oscillate or accommodate for a continuous solution as input. 
For LinearShuntConpensator the value shall be between zero and ShuntCompensator.maximumSections. At value zero the shunt compensator conductance and admittance is zero. Linear interpolation of conductance and admittance between the previous and next integer section is applied in case of non-integer values.
For NonlinearShuntCompensator-s shall only be set to one of the NonlinearShuntCompenstorPoint.sectionNumber. There is no interpolation between NonlinearShuntCompenstorPoint-s.

Attributes.Name: switchOnDate
Attributes.Description: The date and time when the capacitor bank was last switched on.

DerivedEntities.Name: StaticVarCompensator
DerivedEntities.Description:
A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms.

The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint.  The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion.  If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

Attributes.Name: capacitiveRating
Attributes.Description: Capacitive reactance at maximum capacitive reactive power.  Shall always be positive.

Attributes.Name: inductiveRating
Attributes.Description: Inductive reactance at maximum inductive reactive power.  Shall always be negative.

Attributes.Name: slope
Attributes.Description:
The characteristics slope of an SVC defines how the reactive power output changes in proportion to the difference between the regulated bus voltage and the voltage setpoint.
The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

Attributes.Name: voltageSetPoint
Attributes.Description: The reactive power output of the SVC is proportional to the difference between the voltage at the regulated bus and the voltage setpoint.  When the regulated bus voltage is equal to the voltage setpoint, the reactive power output is zero.

Attributes.Name: q
Attributes.Description:
Reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

Attributes.Name: sVCControlMode
Attributes.Description: SVC control mode.

Attributes.Name: controlEnabled
Attributes.Description: Specifies the regulation status of the equipment.  True is regulating, false is not regulating.
