Attributes.Description: Core magnetizing saturation curve knee flux level.

Attributes.Name: xground
Attributes.Description: (for Yn and Zn connections) Reactive part of neutral impedance where 'grounded' is true.

Attributes.Name: endNumber
Attributes.Description: Number for this transformer end, corresponding to the end's order in the power transformer vector group or phase angle clock number.  Highest voltage winding should be 1.  Each end within a power transformer should have a unique subsequent end number.   Note the transformer end number need not match the terminal sequence number.

Attributes.Name: magBaseU
Attributes.Description: The reference voltage at which the magnetizing saturation measurements were made.

Attributes.Name: rground
Attributes.Description: (for Yn and Zn connections) Resistance part of neutral impedance where 'grounded' is true.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransformerMeshImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description:
Transformer mesh impedance (Delta-model) between transformer ends.
The typical case is that this class describes the impedance between two transformer ends pair-wise, i.e. the cardinalities at both transformer end associations are 1. However, in cases where two or more transformer ends are modelled the cardinalities are larger than 1.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Resistance between the 'from' and the 'to' end, seen from the 'from' end.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Reactance between the 'from' and the 'to' end, seen from the 'from' end.

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero-sequence resistance between the 'from' and the 'to' end, seen from the 'from' end.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero-sequence reactance between the 'from' and the 'to' end, seen from the 'from' end.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransformerObservation
DerivedEntities.Description: Common information captured during transformer inspections and/or diagnostics. Note that some properties may be measured through other means and therefore have measurement values in addition to the observed values recorded here.

Attributes.Name: bushingTemp
Attributes.Description: Bushing temperature.

Attributes.Name: dga
Attributes.Description: Dissolved Gas Analysis. Typical values are: Acceptable, Overheating, Corona, Sparking, Arcing.

Attributes.Name: freqResp
Attributes.Description: Frequency Response Analysis. Typical values are: acceptable, slight movement, significant movement, failed, near failure. A graphic of the response diagram, which is a type of document, may be associated with this analysis through the recursive document relationship of the ProcedureDataSet.

Attributes.Name: furfuralDP
Attributes.Description: Overall measure of furfural in oil and mechanical strength of paper. DP, the degree of polymerization, is the strength of the paper. Furfural is a measure of furfural compounds, often expressed in parts per million.

Attributes.Name: hotSpotTemp
Attributes.Description: Hotspot oil temperature.

Attributes.Name: oilColor
Attributes.Description: Oil Quality Analysis-Color.

Attributes.Name: oilDielectricStrength
Attributes.Description: Oil Quality Analysis-Dielectric Strength.

Attributes.Name: oilIFT
Attributes.Description: Oil Quality Analysis- inter facial tension (IFT) - number-Dynes/CM.

Attributes.Name: oilLevel
Attributes.Description: The level of oil in the transformer.

Attributes.Name: oilNeutralizationNumber
Attributes.Description: Oil Quality Analysis-Neutralization Number - Number - Mg KOH.

Attributes.Name: pumpVibration
Attributes.Description: Pump vibration, with typical values being: nominal, high.

Attributes.Name: topOilTemp
Attributes.Description: Top oil temperature.

Attributes.Name: waterContent
Attributes.Description: Water Content expressed in parts per million.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransformerStarImpedance
DerivedEntities.Description:
Transformer star impedance (Pi-model) that accurately reflects impedance for transformers with 2 or 3 windings. For transformers with 4 or more windings, TransformerMeshImpedance class shall be used.
For transmission networks use PowerTransformerEnd impedances (r, r0, x, x0, b, b0, g and g0).

Attributes.Name: r0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series resistance of the transformer end.

Attributes.Name: x0
Attributes.Description: Zero sequence series reactance of the transformer end.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description: Resistance of the transformer end.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the transformer end.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransformerTest
DerivedEntities.Description: Test result for transformer ends, such as short-circuit, open-circuit (excitation) or no-load test.

DerivedEntities.Name: NoLoadTest
DerivedEntities.Description: No-load test results determine core admittance parameters. They include exciting current and core loss measurements from applying voltage to one winding. The excitation may be positive sequence or zero sequence. The test may be repeated at different voltages to measure saturation.

Attributes.Name: energisedEndVoltage
Attributes.Description: Voltage applied to the winding (end) during test.

Attributes.Name: excitingCurrent
Attributes.Description: Exciting current measured from a positive-sequence or single-phase excitation test.

Attributes.Name: excitingCurrentZero
Attributes.Description: Exciting current measured from a zero-sequence open-circuit excitation test.

Attributes.Name: loss
Attributes.Description: Losses measured from a positive-sequence or single-phase excitation test.

Attributes.Name: lossZero
Attributes.Description: Losses measured from a zero-sequence excitation test.

DerivedEntities.Name: OpenCircuitTest
DerivedEntities.Description: Open-circuit test results verify winding turn ratios and phase shifts. They include induced voltage and phase shift measurements on open-circuit windings, with voltage applied to the energised end. For three-phase windings, the excitation can be a positive sequence (the default) or a zero sequence.

Attributes.Name: energisedEndVoltage
Attributes.Description: Voltage applied to the winding (end) during test.

Attributes.Name: openEndVoltage
Attributes.Description: Voltage measured at the open-circuited end, with the energised end set to rated voltage and all other ends open.

Attributes.Name: energisedEndStep
Attributes.Description: Tap step number for the energised end of the test pair.

Attributes.Name: openEndStep
Attributes.Description: Tap step number for the open end of the test pair.

Attributes.Name: phaseShift
Attributes.Description: Phase shift measured at the open end with the energised end set to rated voltage and all other ends open.

DerivedEntities.Name: ShortCircuitTest
DerivedEntities.Description: Short-circuit test results determine mesh impedance parameters. They include load losses and leakage impedances. For three-phase windings, the excitation can be a positive sequence (the default) or a zero sequence. There shall be at least one grounded winding.

Attributes.Name: current
Attributes.Description: Short circuit current..

Attributes.Name: groundedEndStep
Attributes.Description: Tap step number for the grounded end of the test pair.

Attributes.Name: leakageImpedanceZero
Attributes.Description: Leakage impedance measured from a zero-sequence short-circuit test.

Attributes.Name: lossZero
Attributes.Description: Load losses from a zero-sequence short-circuit test.

Attributes.Name: voltage
Attributes.Description: Short circuit voltage..

Attributes.Name: energisedEndStep
Attributes.Description: Tap step number for the energised end of the test pair.

Attributes.Name: leakageImpedance
Attributes.Description: Leakage impedance measured from a positive-sequence or single-phase short-circuit test.

Attributes.Name: loss
Attributes.Description: Load losses from a positive-sequence or single-phase short-circuit test.

Attributes.Name: power
Attributes.Description: Short circuit apparent power.

Attributes.Name: basePower
Attributes.Description: Base power at which the tests are conducted, usually equal to the rateds of one of the involved transformer ends.

Attributes.Name: temperature
Attributes.Description: Temperature at which the test is conducted.

DerivedEntities.Name: TransmissionPath
DerivedEntities.Description: An electrical connection, link, or line consisting of one or more parallel transmission elements between two areas of the interconnected electric systems, or portions thereof. TransmissionCorridor and TransmissionRightOfWay refer to legal aspects. The TransmissionPath refers to the segments between a TransmissionProvider's ServicePoints.

Attributes.Name: availTransferCapability
Attributes.Description: The available transmission capability of a transmission path for the reference direction.

Attributes.Name: parallelPathFlag
Attributes.Description: Flag which indicates if the transmission path is also a designated interconnection "parallel path".

Attributes.Name: totalTransferCapability
Attributes.Description: The total transmission capability of a transmission path in the reference direction.

Attributes.Name: transmissionProductType
Attributes.Description: Type of the transmission product. This could be a transmission service class (firm, total transmission capability, or non-firm), transmission service period (on-peak, full-period, off-peak), transmission service increments (yearly extended, hourly fixed, monthly sliding, etc.), transmission service type (network, available transmission capability, or point-to-point, or a transmission service window (fixed hourly, sliding weekly, extended monthly, etc.).

DerivedEntities.Name: TransmissionRightChain
DerivedEntities.Description: Allows chaining of TransmissionContractRights. Many individual contract rights can be included in the definition of a TransmissionRightChain. A TransmissionRightChain is also defined as a TransmissionContractRight itself.

DerivedEntities.Name: TriggerCondition
DerivedEntities.Description: A conditions that can trigger remedial actions.

DerivedEntities.Name: TypeAssetCatalogue
DerivedEntities.Description: Catalogue of generic types of assets (TypeAsset) that may be used for design purposes. It is not associated with a particular manufacturer.

DerivedEntities.Name: UnavailabilitySwitchAction
DerivedEntities.Description: Relevant switching action for supporting the availability (or unavailability) plans.  This could open or close a switch that is not directly connected to the unavailable equipment .

Attributes.Name: open
Attributes.Description: The switch is to be open during the scheduled period.

DerivedEntities.Name: UnavailablitySchedule
DerivedEntities.Description: A schedule of unavailability for one or more specified equipment that need to follow the same scheduling periods.

DerivedEntities.Name: UnitInitialConditions
DerivedEntities.Description: Resource status at the end of a given clearing period.

Attributes.Name: cumEnergy
Attributes.Description: Cumulative energy production over trading period.

Attributes.Name: cumStatusChanges
Attributes.Description: Cumulative number of status changes of the resource.

Attributes.Name: numberOfStartups
Attributes.Description: Number of start ups in the Operating Day until the end of previous hour.

Attributes.Name: onlineStatus
Attributes.Description: 'true' if the GeneratingUnit is currently On-Line

Attributes.Name: resourceMW
Attributes.Description: Resource MW output at the end of previous clearing period.

Attributes.Name: resourceStatus
Attributes.Description:
Resource status at the end of previous clearing period:
0 - off-line
1 - on-line production
2 - in shutdown process
3 - in startup process

Attributes.Name: statusDate
Attributes.Description: Time and date for resourceStatus

Attributes.Name: timeInStatus
Attributes.Description: Time in market trading intervals the resource is in the state as of the end of the previous clearing period.

Attributes.Name: timeInterval
Attributes.Description: Time interval

DerivedEntities.Name: UsagePoint
DerivedEntities.Description: Logical or physical point in the network to which readings or events may be attributed. Used at the place where a physical or virtual meter may be located; however, it is not required that a meter be present.

DerivedEntities.Name: MarketEvaluationPoint
DerivedEntities.Description: The identification of an entity where energy products are measured or computed.

Attributes.Name: checkBilling
Attributes.Description: True if as a result of an inspection or otherwise, there is a reason to suspect that a previous billing may have been performed with erroneous data. Value should be reset once this potential discrepancy has been resolved.

Attributes.Name: connectionState
Attributes.Description: State of the usage point with respect to connection to the network.

Attributes.Name: estimatedLoad
Attributes.Description: Estimated load.

Attributes.Name: isSdp
Attributes.Description: If true, this usage point is a service delivery point, i.e., a usage point where the ownership of the service changes hands.

Attributes.Name: minimalUsageExpected
Attributes.Description: If true, minimal or zero usage is expected at this usage point for situations such as premises vacancy, logical or physical disconnect. It is used for readings validation and estimation.

Attributes.Name: outageRegion
Attributes.Description: Outage region in which this usage point is located.

Attributes.Name: phaseCount
Attributes.Description: Number of potential phases the Usage Point supports, typically 0, 1 or 3.

Attributes.Name: ratedCurrent
Attributes.Description: Current flow that this usage point is configured to deliver.

Attributes.Name: readRoute
Attributes.Description: Identifier of the route to which this usage point is assigned for purposes of meter reading. Typically used to configure hand held meter reading systems prior to collection of reads.

Attributes.Name: serviceDeliveryRemark
Attributes.Description: Remarks about this usage point, for example the reason for it being rated with a non-nominal priority.

Attributes.Name: amiBillingReady
Attributes.Description: Tracks the lifecycle of the metering installation at a usage point with respect to readiness for billing via advanced metering infrastructure reads.

Attributes.Name: connectionCategory
Attributes.Description: A code used to specify the connection category, e.g., low voltage or low pressure, where the usage point is defined.

Attributes.Name: disconnectionMethod
Attributes.Description: Is an indication of how the usage point is physically connected or disconnected.

Attributes.Name: grounded
Attributes.Description: True if grounded.

Attributes.Name: isVirtual
Attributes.Description: If true, this usage point is virtual, i.e., no physical location exists in the network where a meter could be located to collect the meter readings. For example, one may define a virtual usage point to serve as an aggregation of usage for all of a company's premises distributed widely across the distribution territory. Otherwise, the usage point is physical, i.e., there is a logical point in the network where a meter could be located to collect meter readings.

Attributes.Name: nominalServiceVoltage
Attributes.Description: Nominal service voltage.

Attributes.Name: phaseCode
Attributes.Description: Phase code. Number of wires and specific nominal phases can be deduced from enumeration literal values. For example, ABCN is three-phase, four-wire, s12n (splitSecondary12N) is single-phase, three-wire, and s1n and s2n are single-phase, two-wire.

Attributes.Name: physicalConnectionCapacity
Attributes.Description: Quantitative information about the maximum physical capacity of the connection for the usage point.

Attributes.Name: ratedPower
Attributes.Description: Active power that this usage point is configured to deliver.

Attributes.Name: readCycle
Attributes.Description: Cycle day on which the meter for this usage point will normally be read.  Usually correlated with the billing cycle.

Attributes.Name: servicePriority
Attributes.Description: Priority of service for this usage point. Note that usage points at the same service location can have different priorities.

DerivedEntities.Name: UsagePointGroup
DerivedEntities.Description: Abstraction for management of group communications within a two-way AMR system or the data for a group of related usage points. Commands can be issued to all of the usage points that belong to a usage point group using a defined group address and the underlying AMR communication infrastructure.

Attributes.Name: type
Attributes.Description: Type of this group.

DerivedEntities.Name: ValueAliasSet
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes the translation of a set of values into a name and is intendend to facilitate custom translations. Each ValueAliasSet has a name, description etc. A specific Measurement may represent a discrete state like Open, Closed, Intermediate etc. This requires a translation from the MeasurementValue.value number to a string, e.g. 0->"Invalid", 1->"Open", 2->"Closed", 3->"Intermediate". Each ValueToAlias member in ValueAliasSet.Value describe a mapping for one particular value to a name.

DerivedEntities.Name: ValueToAlias
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes the translation of one particular value into a name, e.g. 1 as "Open".

Attributes.Name: value
Attributes.Description: The value that is mapped.

DerivedEntities.Name: Vendor
DerivedEntities.Description: The entity that owns the point of sale and contracts with the cashier to receipt payments and vend tokens using the payment system. The vendor has a private contract with and is managed by the merchant which is a type of organisation. The vendor is accountable to the merchant for revenue collected, and the merchant is in turn accountable to the supplier.

DerivedEntities.Name: VisibilityLayer
DerivedEntities.Description:
Layers are typically used for grouping diagram objects according to themes and scales. Themes are used to display or hide certain information (e.g., lakes, borders), while scales are used for hiding or displaying information depending on the current zoom level (hide text when it is too small to be read, or when it exceeds the screen size). This is also called de-cluttering.
CIM based graphics exchange supports an m:n relationship between diagram objects and layers. The importing system shall convert an m:n case into an appropriate 1:n representation if the importing system does not support m:n.

Attributes.Name: drawingOrder
Attributes.Description: The drawing order for this layer.  The higher the number, the later the layer and the objects within it are rendered.

DerivedEntities.Name: WheelingCounterParty
DerivedEntities.Description: Counter party in a wheeling transaction.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindAeroConstIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Constant aerodynamic torque model which assumes that the aerodynamic torque is constant.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.1.1.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindAeroOneDimIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
One-dimensional aerodynamic model.  
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.1.2.

Attributes.Name: ka
Attributes.Description: Aerodynamic gain (ka). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetaomega
Attributes.Description: Initial pitch angle (thetaomega0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindAeroTwoDimIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Two-dimensional aerodynamic model.  
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.1.3.

Attributes.Name: dpomega
Attributes.Description: Partial derivative of aerodynamic power with respect to changes in WTR speed (dpomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dpv1
Attributes.Description: Partial derivative (dpv1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: pavail
Attributes.Description: Available aerodynamic power (pavail). It is a case-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dptheta
Attributes.Description: Partial derivative of aerodynamic power with respect to changes in pitch angle (dptheta). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: omegazero
Attributes.Description: Rotor speed if the wind turbine is not derated (omega0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetazero
Attributes.Description: Pitch angle if the wind turbine is not derated (theta0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetav2
Attributes.Description: Blade angle at twice rated wind speed (thetav2). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContCurrLimIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Current limitation model.  The current limitation model combines the physical limits and the control limits.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.8.

Attributes.Name: imax
Attributes.Description: Maximum continuous current at the wind turbine terminals (imax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpqu
Attributes.Description: Partial derivative of reactive current limit (Kpqu) versus voltage. It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: mqpri
Attributes.Description: Prioritisation of Q control during UVRT (Mqpri). It is a project-dependent parameter. true = reactive power priority (1 in the IEC model) false = active power priority (0 in the IEC model).

Attributes.Name: upqumax
Attributes.Description: Wind turbine voltage in the operation point where zero reactive current can be delivered (upqumax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: imaxdip
Attributes.Description: Maximum current during voltage dip at the wind turbine terminals (imaxdip). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: mdfslim
Attributes.Description: Limitation of type 3 stator current (MDFSLim). MDFSLim = 1 for wind turbines type 4. It is a type-dependent parameter. false= total current limitation (0 in the IEC model) true=stator current limitation (1 in the IEC model).

Attributes.Name: tufiltcl
Attributes.Description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltcl) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContPitchAngleIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Pitch angle control model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.2.

Attributes.Name: kic
Attributes.Description: Power PI controller integration gain (KIc). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpx
Attributes.Description: Pitch cross coupling gain (KPX). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: ttheta
Attributes.Description: Pitch time constant (ttheta) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dthetamax
Attributes.Description: Maximum pitch positive ramp rate (dthetamax) (> WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamin). It is a type-dependent parameter. Unit = degrees / s.

Attributes.Name: kiomega
Attributes.Description: Speed PI controller integration gain (KIomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpomega
Attributes.Description: Speed PI controller proportional gain (KPomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetamin
Attributes.Description: Minimum pitch angle (thetamin) (< WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dthetamin
Attributes.Description: Maximum pitch negative ramp rate (dthetamin) (< WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamax). It is a type-dependent parameter. Unit = degrees / s.

Attributes.Name: kpc
Attributes.Description: Power PI controller proportional gain (KPc). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetamax
Attributes.Description: Maximum pitch angle (thetamax) (> WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContPType3IEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
P control model type 3.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.4.

Attributes.Name: dpmax
Attributes.Description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dthetamax
Attributes.Description: Ramp limitation of torque, required in some grid codes (dtmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kip
Attributes.Description: PI controller integration parameter (KIp). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: pdtdmax
Attributes.Description: Maximum active drive train damping power (pDTDmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetauscale
Attributes.Description: Voltage scaling factor of reset-torque (tuscale). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tufiltp3
Attributes.Description: Filter time constant for voltage measurement (Tufiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dprefmax
Attributes.Description: Maximum ramp rate of wind turbine reference power (dprefmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dthetamaxuvrt
Attributes.Description: Limitation of torque rise rate during UVRT (dthetamaxUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: mpuvrt
Attributes.Description: Enable UVRT power control mode (MpUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter. true = voltage control (1 in the IEC model) false = reactive power control (0 in the IEC model).

Attributes.Name: omegaoffset
Attributes.Description: Offset to reference value that limits controller action during rotor speed changes (omegaoffset). It is a case-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tdvs
Attributes.Description: Time delay after deep voltage sags (TDVS) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tomegafiltp3
Attributes.Description: Filter time constant for generator speed measurement (Tomegafiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpfiltp3
Attributes.Description: Filter time constant for power measurement (Tpfiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: updip
Attributes.Description: Voltage dip threshold for P-control (uPdip). Part of turbine control, often different (e.g 0.8) from converter thresholds. It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: dprefmin
Attributes.Description: Minimum ramp rate of wind turbine reference power (dprefmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kdtd
Attributes.Description: Gain for active drive train damping (KDTD). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpp
Attributes.Description: PI controller proportional gain (KPp). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: omegadtd
Attributes.Description: Active drive train damping frequency (omegaDTD). It can be calculated from two mass model parameters. It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: thetaemin
Attributes.Description: Minimum electrical generator torque (temin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tomegaref
Attributes.Description: Time constant in speed reference filter (Tomega,ref) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpord
Attributes.Description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpord). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: udvs
Attributes.Description: Voltage limit for hold UVRT status after deep voltage sags (uDVS). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: zeta
Attributes.Description: Coefficient for active drive train damping (zeta). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContPType4aIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
P control model type 4A.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.5.

Attributes.Name: dpmaxp4a
Attributes.Description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmaxp4A). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tufiltp4a
Attributes.Description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltp4A) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpordp4a
Attributes.Description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpordp4A) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContPType4bIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
P control model type 4B.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.6.

Attributes.Name: dpmaxp4b
Attributes.Description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmaxp4B). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpaero
Attributes.Description: Time constant in aerodynamic power response (Tpaero) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpordp4b
Attributes.Description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpordp4B) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tufiltp4b
Attributes.Description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltp4B) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContQIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Q control model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.7.

Attributes.Name: iqh1
Attributes.Description: Maximum reactive current injection during dip (iqh1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: iqmax
Attributes.Description: Maximum reactive current injection (iqmax) (> WindContQIEC.iqmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kiu
Attributes.Description: Voltage PI controller integration gain (KI,u). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpu
Attributes.Description: Voltage PI controller proportional gain (KP,u). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: rdroop
Attributes.Description: Resistive component of voltage drop impedance (rdroop) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpost
Attributes.Description: Length of time period where post fault reactive power is injected (Tpost) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tufiltq
Attributes.Description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltq) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: udb2
Attributes.Description: Voltage deadband upper limit (udb2). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: uqdip
Attributes.Description: Voltage threshold for UVRT detection in Q control (uqdip). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: uref0
Attributes.Description: User-defined bias in voltage reference (uref0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: xdroop
Attributes.Description: Inductive component of voltage drop impedance (xdroop) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: iqmin
Attributes.Description: Minimum reactive current injection (iqmin) (< WindContQIEC.iqmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: iqpost
Attributes.Description: Post fault reactive current injection (iqpost). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kiq
Attributes.Description: Reactive power PI controller integration gain (KI,q). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kpq
Attributes.Description: Reactive power PI controller proportional gain (KP,q). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: kqv
Attributes.Description: Voltage scaling factor for UVRT current (Kqv). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tpfiltq
Attributes.Description: Power measurement filter time constant (Tpfiltq) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tqord
Attributes.Description: Time constant in reactive power order lag (Tqord) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: udb1
Attributes.Description: Voltage deadband lower limit (udb1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: umax
Attributes.Description: Maximum voltage in voltage PI controller integral term (umax) (> WindContQIEC.umin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: umin
Attributes.Description: Minimum voltage in voltage PI controller integral term (umin) (< WindContQIEC.umax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: windQcontrolModesType
Attributes.Description: Types of general wind turbine Q control modes (MqG). It is a project-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: windUVRTQcontrolModesType
Attributes.Description: Types of UVRT Q control modes (MqUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContQLimIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
Constant Q limitation model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.9.

Attributes.Name: qmax
Attributes.Description: Maximum reactive power (qmax) (> WindContQLimIEC.qmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: qmin
Attributes.Description: Minimum reactive power (qmin) (< WindContQLimIEC.qmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

DerivedEntities.Name: WindContQPQULimIEC
DerivedEntities.Description:
QP and QU limitation model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

Attributes.Name: tpfiltql
Attributes.Description: Power measurement filter time constant for Q capacity (Tpfiltql) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

Attributes.Name: tufiltql

Entities.Name: PhaseCode
Entities.Description:
An unordered enumeration of phase identifiers.  Allows designation of phases for both transmission and distribution equipment, circuits and loads.   The enumeration, by itself, does not describe how the phases are connected together or connected to ground.  Ground is not explicitly denoted as a phase.
Residential and small commercial loads are often served from single-phase, or split-phase, secondary circuits. For the example of s12N, phases 1 and 2 refer to hot wires that are 180 degrees out of phase, while N refers to the neutral wire. Through single-phase transformer connections, these secondary circuits may be served from one or two of the primary phases A, B, and C. For three-phase loads, use the A, B, C phase codes instead of s12N.
The integer values are from IEC 61968-9 to support revenue metering applications.

Entities.Description:
Type of name. Possible values for attribute 'name' are implementation dependent but standard profiles may specify types. An enterprise may have multiple IT systems each having its own local name for the same object, e.g. a planning system may have different names from an EMS. An object may also have different names within the same IT system, e.g. localName as defined in CIM version 14. The definition from CIM14 is:
The localName is a human readable name of the object. It is a free text name local to a node in a naming hierarchy similar to a file directory structure. A power system related naming hierarchy may be: Substation, VoltageLevel, Equipment etc. Children of the same parent in such a hierarchy have names that typically are unique among them.

Attributes.Name: QUESTIONABLE

Attributes.Name: GOOD
Attributes.Description: The value is marked good if no abnormal condition of the acquisition function or the information source is detected.

Attributes.Name: INVALID
Attributes.Description: The value is marked invalid when a supervision function recognises abnormal conditions of the acquisition function or the information source (missing or non-operating updating devices). The value is not defined under this condition. The mark invalid is used to indicate to the client that the value may be incorrect and shall not be used.

DerivedEntities.Description: Measurement quality flags for Analog Values.

Attributes.Name: scadaQualityCode
Attributes.Description: The quality code for the given Analog Value.

DerivedEntities.Name: DiscreteMeasurementValueQuality

Attributes.Name: manualReplaceIndicator
Attributes.Description: Switch Manual Replace Indicator. Flag indicating that the switch is manual replace.

Attributes.Name: removeFromOperationIndicator
Attributes.Description: Removed From Operation Indicator. Flag indicating that the switch is removed from operation.

Attributes.Name: oldData
Attributes.Description: Measurement value is old and possibly invalid, as it has not been successfully updated during a specified time interval.

Attributes.Name: oscillatory
Attributes.Description: To prevent some overload of the communication it is sensible to detect and suppress oscillating (fast changing) binary inputs. If a signal changes in a defined time twice in the same direction (from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0) then oscillation is detected and the detail quality identifier "oscillatory" is set. If it is detected a configured numbers of transient changes could be passed by. In this time the validity status "questionable" is set. If after this defined numbers of changes the signal is still in the oscillating state the value shall be set either to the opposite state of the previous stable value or to a defined default value. In this case the validity status "questionable" is reset and "invalid" is set as long as the signal is oscillating. If it is configured such that no transient changes should be passed by then the validity status "invalid" is set immediately in addition to the detail quality identifier "oscillatory" (used for status information only).

Attributes.Name: overFlow
Attributes.Description: Measurement value is beyond the capability of being  represented properly. For example, a counter value overflows from maximum count back to a value of zero.

Attributes.Name: suspect
Attributes.Description: A correlation function has detected that the value is not consistent with other values. Typically set by a network State Estimator.

Attributes.Name: validity
Attributes.Description: Validity of the measurement value.

Attributes.Name: badReference
Attributes.Description: Measurement value may be incorrect due to a reference being out of calibration.

Attributes.Name: estimatorReplaced
Attributes.Description: Value has been replaced by State Estimator. estimatorReplaced is not an IEC61850 quality bit but has been put in this class for convenience.

Attributes.Name: failure
Attributes.Description: This identifier indicates that a supervision function has detected an internal or external failure, e.g. communication failure.

Attributes.Name: operatorBlocked
Attributes.Description: Measurement value is blocked and hence unavailable for transmission.

Attributes.Name: outOfRange
Attributes.Description: Measurement value is beyond a predefined range of value.

Attributes.Name: source
Attributes.Description: Source gives information related to the origin of a value. The value may be acquired from the process, defaulted or substituted.

Attributes.Name: test
Attributes.Description: Measurement value is transmitted for test purposes.

DerivedEntities.Name: RatioTapChangerTablePoint
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes each tap step in the ratio tap changer tabular curve.

Attributes.Name: b
Attributes.Description:
The magnetizing branch susceptance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual susceptance is calculated as follows:
calculated magnetizing susceptance = b(nominal) * (1 + b(from this class)/100).   The b(nominal) is defined as the static magnetizing susceptance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

Attributes.Name: g
Attributes.Description:
The magnetizing branch conductance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual conductance is calculated as follows:
calculated magnetizing conductance = g(nominal) * (1 + g(from this class)/100).   The g(nominal) is defined as the static magnetizing conductance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

Attributes.Name: r
Attributes.Description:
The resistance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual reactance is calculated as follows:
calculated resistance = r(nominal) * (1 + r(from this class)/100).   The r(nominal) is defined as the static resistance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

Attributes.Name: ratio
Attributes.Description:
The voltage at the tap step divided by rated voltage of the transformer end having the tap changer. Hence this is a value close to one.
For example, if the ratio at step 1 is 1.01, and the rated voltage of the transformer end is 110kV, then the voltage obtained by setting the tap changer to step 1 to is 111.1kV.

Attributes.Name: step
Attributes.Description: The tap step.

Attributes.Name: x
Attributes.Description:
The series reactance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual reactance is calculated as follows:
calculated reactance = x(nominal) * (1 + x(from this class)/100).   The x(nominal) is defined as the static series reactance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

Entities.Name: PhaseImpedanceData
Entities.Description:
Impedance and conductance matrix element values. 
The diagonal elements are described by the elements having the same toPhase and fromPhase value and the off diagonal elements have different toPhase and fromPhase values.  The matrix can also be stored in symmetric lower triangular format using the row and column attributes, which map to ACLineSegmentPhase.sequenceNumber.

Attributes.Name: row

Minimum MW for a load reduction (e.g., MW rating of a discrete pump.

This attribute may be used also in the LoadBid class. The reason that the attribute is also modeled in this class is that it is resource attribute and needs to be persistently stored.

Attributes.Name: minLoadReductionInterval
Attributes.Description:
Shortest period load reduction shall be maintained before load can be restored to normal levels.

This attribute may be used also in the LoadBid class. The reason that the attribute is also modeled in this class is that it is resource attribute and needs to be persistently stored.

Attributes.Name: minTimeBetLoadRed
Attributes.Description:
Shortest time that load shall be left at normal levels before a new load reduction.

This attribute may be used also in the LoadBid class. The reason that the attribute is also modeled in this class is that it is resource attribute and needs to be persistently stored.

Attributes.Name: maxBaseLoad
Attributes.Description: Maximum Base Load (MW), per Participating Load Resource

Attributes.Name: maxDeploymentTime
Attributes.Description: Maximum Deployment time (seconds)

Attributes.Name: maxLoadReduction
Attributes.Description: maximum load reduction

Attributes.Name: maxWeeklyDeployment
Attributes.Description: Maximum weekly deployments

Attributes.Name: minLoadReductionCost
Attributes.Description: minimum load reduction cost. Single number for the load

Attributes.Name: minReductionTime
Attributes.Description: Minimum Load Reduction Time (min), per Participating Load Resource

Attributes.Name: reqNoticeTime
Attributes.Description:
Time period that is required from an order to reduce a load to the time that it takes to get to the minimum load reduction.

This attribute may be used also in the LoadBid class. The reason that the attribute is also modeled in this class is that it is resource attribute and needs to be persistently stored.

Entities.Name: DataSet
Entities.Description:
A generic container of a version of instance data. The MRID can be used in an audit trail, not in reusable script intended to work with new versions of data.
A dataset could be serialized multiple times and in multiple technologies, yet retain the same identity.

DerivedEntities.Name: ChangeSet
DerivedEntities.Description: Describes a set of changes that can be applied in different situations.   A given registered target object  MRID may only be referenced once by the contained change set members.

DerivedEntities.Name: InstanceSet
DerivedEntities.Description: Instance of a version of a model part.   This corresponds to a payload of instance data.

Attributes.Name: description
Attributes.Description: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

Attributes.Name: mRID
Attributes.Description:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID,  as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552 Edition 1, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

Attributes.Name: name
Attributes.Description: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

Attributes.Name: majorVersion
Attributes.Description: The universal CIM version name describing a consistent set of packages.

Attributes.Name: minorVersion
Attributes.Description: Describe minor updates and error corrections.

Attributes.Name: published
Attributes.Description:
The date when the complete CIM canonical model is published and made available for use, 
After the publication the major version and name space are updated.

Entities.Name: ChangeSetMember
Entities.Description: A CRUD-style data object.

DerivedEntities.Description: An object is to be created in the context.

DerivedEntities.Name: ObjectDeletion
DerivedEntities.Description: An object is to be deleted in the context.

DerivedEntities.Description: The object already exists and is to be modified.

Entities.Name: ProprietaryParameterDynamics
Entities.Description:
Supports definition of one or more parameters of several different datatypes for use by proprietary user-defined models.  
This class does not inherit from IdentifiedObject since it is not intended that a single instance of it be referenced by more than one proprietary user-defined model instance.

Attributes.Name: booleanParameterValue
Attributes.Description: Boolean parameter value. If this attribute is populated, integerParameterValue and floatParameterValue will not be.

Attributes.Name: integerParameterValue
Attributes.Description: Integer parameter value.  If this attribute is populated, booleanParameterValue and floatParameterValue will not be.

Attributes.Name: floatParameterValue
Attributes.Description: Floating point parameter value.  If this attribute is populated, booleanParameterValue and integerParameterValue will not be.

Attributes.Name: parameterNumber
Attributes.Description: Sequence number of the parameter among the set of parameters associated with the related proprietary user-defined model.

Entities.Name: StateVariable
Entities.Description: An abstract class for state variables.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvInjection
DerivedEntities.Description: The SvInjection reports the calculated bus injection minus the sum of the terminal flows. The terminal flow is positive out from the bus (load sign convention) and bus injection has positive flow into the bus. SvInjection may have the remainder after state estimation or slack after power flow calculation.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The terminal phase at which the connection is applied.   If missing, the injection is assumed to be balanced among non-neutral phases.

Attributes.Name: qInjection
Attributes.Description: The reactive power mismatch between calculated injection and initial injection.  Positive sign means injection into the TopologicalNode (bus).

Attributes.Name: pInjection
Attributes.Description: The active power mismatch between calculated injection and initial injection.  Positive sign means injection into the TopologicalNode (bus).

DerivedEntities.Name: SvPowerFlow
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for power flow. Load convention is used for flow direction. This means flow out from the TopologicalNode into the equipment is positive.

Attributes.Name: p
Attributes.Description: The active power flow. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

Attributes.Name: q
Attributes.Description: The reactive power flow. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The individual phase of the flow.   If unspecified, then assumed to be balanced among phases.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvShuntCompensatorSections
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for the number of sections in service for a shunt compensator.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The terminal phase at which the connection is applied.   If missing, the injection is assumed to be balanced among non-neutral phases.

Attributes.Name: sections
Attributes.Description: The number of sections in service as a continuous variable. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. To get integer value scale with ShuntCompensator.bPerSection.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvStatus
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for status.

Attributes.Name: inService
Attributes.Description: The in service status as a result of topology processing.  It indicates if the equipment is considered as energized by the power flow. It reflects if the equipment is connected within a solvable island.  It does not necessarily reflect whether or not the island was solved by the power flow.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The individual phase status.    If the attribute is unspecified, then three phase model is assumed.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvSwitch
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for switch.

Attributes.Name: open
Attributes.Description: The attribute tells if the computed state of the switch is considered open.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: The terminal phase at which the connection is applied.   If missing, the injection is assumed to be balanced among non-neutral phases.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvTapStep
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for transformer tap step.

Attributes.Name: position
Attributes.Description: The floating point tap position.   This is not the tap ratio, but rather the tap step position as defined by the related tap changer model and normally is constrained to be within the range of minimum and maximum tap positions.

DerivedEntities.Name: SvVoltage
DerivedEntities.Description: State variable for voltage.

Attributes.Name: phase
Attributes.Description: If specified the voltage is the line to ground voltage of the individual phase.   If unspecified, then the voltage is assumed balanced.

Attributes.Name: angle
Attributes.Description: The voltage angle of the topological node complex voltage with respect to system reference.

Attributes.Name: v
Attributes.Description: The voltage magnitude at the topological node. The attribute shall be a positive value.

Attributes.Name: degC
Attributes.Description:
Relative temperature in degrees Celsius.
In the SI unit system the symbol is ºC. Electric charge is measured in coulomb that has the unit symbol C. To distinguish degree Celsius form coulomb the symbol used in the UML is degC. Reason for not using ºC is the special character º is difficult to manage in software.

Attributes.Name: Hz

Attributes.Name: W

Attributes.Name: VA
Attributes.Description: Apparent power in Volt Ampere (See also real power and reactive power.)

Attributes.Name: VAr
Attributes.Description:
Reactive power in Volt Ampere reactive. The “reactive” or “imaginary” component of electrical power (VIsin(phi)). (See also real power and apparent power).
Note: Different meter designs use different methods to arrive at their results. Some meters may compute reactive power as an arithmetic value, while others compute the value vectorially. The data consumer should determine the method in use and the suitability of the measurement for the intended purpose.

Attributes.Name: Vs

Attributes.Description: Time, minute  = 60 s.

Attributes.Name: Q

Attributes.Description: Quantity energy, Qh.

Attributes.Description: resistivity, Ohm metre, (rho).

Attributes.Name: Btu

Attributes.Name: therm

Attributes.Description: Operating reserve requirement in MW, where operating reserve is the generating capability that is fully available within 30 minutes. Operating reserve is composed of primary reserve (t less than 10 min) and secondary reserve (10 less than t less than 30 min).

Attributes.Name: isFreeSequence
Attributes.Description: For a step, if isFreeSequence is set to false or is not specified, all of the steps in the group must be executed in the order defined by the sequenceNumber attribute. The sequenceNumber for a step has a different meaning when there are two or more sequential steps that have the isFreeSequence attribute set to true. Execution must still be performed in sequenceNumber order until a set of two or more steps that have isFreeSequence set to true is encountered. In this case, these steps can be executed in any sequence, until a step is encountered that has isFreeSequence set to false. All of the steps preceding this step must be executed before the step can be executed.

Attributes.Name: sequenceNumber
Attributes.Description: Order of this activity in the sequence of activities within the switching plan.

Value other than 'none' is typically used to mitigate potential deleterious effects of simultaneous operation of multiple devices.

Attributes.Name: start
Attributes.Description: Start time of an event or control action affecting one or more multiple devices is randomised.

Attributes.Name: end
Attributes.Description: End time of an event or control action affecting one or more devices is randomised to prevent simultaneous operation.

Attributes.Name: startAndEnd
Attributes.Description: Both the start time and the end time of an event or control action affecting one or more devices are randomised to prevent simultaneous operation.

Attributes.Name: default
Attributes.Description: Randomisation of start and/or end times involving the operation of one or more devices is controlled by default settings for the device(s).

Attributes.Name: none
Attributes.Description: Neither the start time nor the end time of an event or control action affecting one or more devices is randomised.

Entities.Name: ReadingQuality
Entities.Description: Quality of a specific reading value or interval reading value. Note that more than one quality may be applicable to a given reading. Typically not used unless problems or unusual conditions occur (i.e., quality for each reading is assumed to be good unless stated otherwise in associated reading quality type). It can also be used with the corresponding reading quality type to indicate that the validation has been performed and succeeded.

Attributes.Name: source
Attributes.Description: System acting as the source of the quality code.

Attributes.Name: comment
Attributes.Description: Elaboration on the quality code.

Attributes.Name: timeStamp
Attributes.Description: Date and time at which the quality code was assigned or ascertained.

Entities.Name: AccumulationKind
Entities.Description: Kind of accumulation behaviour for read / measured values from individual end points.

Attributes.Name: none
Attributes.Description: Not applicable, or implied by the unit of measure.

Attributes.Name: bulkQuantity
Attributes.Description:
A value from a register which represents the bulk quantity of a commodity. This quantity is computed as the integral of the commodity usage rate. This value is typically used as the basis for the dial reading at the meter, and as a result, will roll over upon reaching a maximum dial value. 
Note 1: With the metering system, the roll-over behaviour typically implies a roll-under behavior so that the value presented is always a positive value (e.g. unsigned integer or positive decimal.) However, when communicating data between enterprise applications a negative value might occur in a case such as net metering.
Note 2: A 'bulkQuantity' refers primarily to the dial reading and not the consumption over a specific period of time.

Attributes.Name: continuousCumulative
Attributes.Description:
The sum of the previous billing period values and the present period value.
Note: 'continuousCumulative' is commonly used in conjunction with 'demand', and it  would represent the cumulative sum of the previous billing period maximum demand values (as occurring with each demand reset) summed with the present period maximum demand value (which has yet to be reset.)

Attributes.Name: cumulative
Attributes.Description:
The sum of the previous billing period values.
Note: 'cumulative' is commonly used in conjunction with “demand.” Each demand reset causes the maximum demand value for the present billing period (since the last demand reset) to accumulate as an accumulative total of all maximum demands. So instead of 'zeroing' the demand register, a demand reset has the effect of adding the present maximum demand to this accumulating total.

Attributes.Name: deltaData
Attributes.Description:
The difference between the value at the end of the prescribed interval and the beginning of the interval. This is used for incremental interval data. 
Note: One common application would be for load profile data, another use might be to report the number of events within an interval (such as the number of equipment energisations within the specified period of time.)

Attributes.Name: indicating
Attributes.Description:
As if a needle is swung out on the meter face to a value to indicate the current value.
Note: An 'indicating' value is typically measured over hundreds of milliseconds or greater, or may imply a “pusher” mechanism to capture a value. Compare this to 'instantaneous' which is measured over a shorter period of time.

Attributes.Name: summation
Attributes.Description:
A form of accumulation which is selective with respect to time. 
Note : 'summation' could be considered a specialisation of 'bulkQuantity' as it selectively accumulates pulses over a timing pattern (while 'bulkQuantity' accumulates pulses all of the time).

Attributes.Name: timeDelay
Attributes.Description: A form of computation which introduces a time delay characteristic to the data value.

Attributes.Name: instantaneous
Attributes.Description:
Typically measured over the fastest period of time allowed by the definition of the metric (usually milliseconds or tens of milliseconds.)
Note: 'instantaneous' was moved to attribute #3 in Ed.2 of IEC 61968-9, from attribute #1 in Ed.1 of IEC 61968-9.

Attributes.Name: latchingQuantity
Attributes.Description:
When this description is applied to a metered value, it implies that the value is a time-independent cumulative quantity much like a 'bulkQuantity', except that it latches upon the maximum value upon reaching that value. Any additional accumulation (positive or negative) is discarded until a reset occurs. 
Note: A 'latchingQuantity' may also occur in the downward direction – upon reaching a minimum value. The terms 'maximum' or 'minimum' (for 'aggregate') will usually be included when this type of accumulation behaviour is present. 
When this description is applied to an encoded value (UOM= 'Code'), it implies that the value has one or more bits which are latching. The condition that caused the bit to be set may have long since evaporated.
In either case, the timestamp that accompanies the value may not coincide with the moment the value was initially set.
In both cases a system will need to perform an operation to clear the latched value.

Attributes.Name: boundedQuantity
Attributes.Description: A time-independent cumulative quantity much like a 'bulkQuantity' or a 'latchingQuantity', except that the accumulation stops at the maximum or minimum values. When the maximum is reached, any additional positive accumulation is discarded, but negative accumulation may be accepted (thus lowering the counter.) Likewise, when the negative bound is reached, any additional negative accumulation is discarded, but positive accumulation is accepted (thus increasing the counter.)

Entities.Name: FlowDirectionKind
Entities.Description: Kind of flow direction for reading/measured  values proper to some commodities such as, for example, energy, power, demand.

Attributes.Name: forward
Attributes.Description: "Delivered," or "Imported" as defined 61968-2. Forward Active Energy is a positive kWh value as one would naturally expect to find as energy is supplied by the utility and consumed at the service. Forward Reactive Energy is a positive VArh value as one would naturally expect to find in the presence of inductive loading. In polyphase metering, the forward energy register is incremented when the sum of the phase energies is greater than zero:

Attributes.Name: leading
Attributes.Description:
Typically used to describe that a power factor is leading the reference value.
Note: Leading power factors typically indicate capacitive loading.

Attributes.Name: q1plusQ2
Attributes.Description: Reactive positive quadrants. (The term “lagging” is preferred.)

Attributes.Name: q1plusQ4
Attributes.Description: Quadrants 1 and 4 usually represent forward active energy

Attributes.Name: q2plusQ3
Attributes.Description: Quadrants 2 and 3 usually represent reverse active energy

Attributes.Name: q2minusQ3
Attributes.Description: Q2 minus Q3

Attributes.Name: q3minusQ2
Attributes.Description: Q3 minus Q2

Attributes.Name: quadrant2
Attributes.Description: Q2 only

Attributes.Name: reverse
Attributes.Description: Reverse Active Energy is equivalent to "Received," or "Exported" as defined in 61968-2. Reverse Active Energy is a positive kWh value as one would expect to find when energy is backfed by the service onto the utility network. Reverse Reactive Energy is a positive VArh value as one would expect to find in the presence of capacitive loading and a leading Power Factor. In polyphase metering, the reverse energy register is incremented when the sum of the phase energies is less than zero: Note: The value passed as a reverse value is always a positive value. It is understood by the label “reverse” that it represents negative flow.

Attributes.Name: total
Attributes.Description: |Forward| + |Reverse|, See 61968-2. The sum of the commodity in all quadrants Q1+Q2+Q3+Q4. In polyphase metering, the total energy register is incremented when the absolute value of the sum of the phase energies is greater than zero:

Attributes.Name: none
Attributes.Description: Not Applicable (N/A)

Attributes.Name: lagging
Attributes.Description:
Typically used to describe that a power factor is lagging the reference value. 
Note 1: When used to describe VA, “lagging” describes a form of measurement where reactive power is considered in all four quadrants, but real power is considered only in quadrants I and IV.
Note 2: When used to describe power factor, the term “Lagging” implies that the PF is negative. The term “lagging” in this case takes the place of the negative sign. If a signed PF value is to be passed by the data producer, then the direction of flow enumeration zero (none) should be used in order to avoid the possibility of creating an expression that employs a double negative. The data consumer should be able to tell from the sign of the data if the PF is leading or lagging. This principle is analogous to the concept that “Reverse” energy is an implied negative value, and to publish a negative reverse value would be ambiguous.
Note 3: Lagging power factors typically indicate inductive loading.

Attributes.Name: net
Attributes.Description:
|Forward| - |Reverse|, See 61968-2.

Note: In some systems, the value passed as a “net” value could become negative. In other systems the value passed as a “net” value is always a positive number, and rolls-over and rolls-under as needed.

Attributes.Name: q1plusQ3
Attributes.Description: Quadrants 1 and 3

Attributes.Name: q1minusQ4
Attributes.Description: Q1 minus Q4

Attributes.Name: q2plusQ4
Attributes.Description: Quadrants 2 and 4

Attributes.Name: q3plusQ4
Attributes.Description: Reactive negative quadrants. (The term “leading” is preferred.)

Attributes.Name: quadrant1
Attributes.Description: Q1 only

Attributes.Name: quadrant3
Attributes.Description: Q3 only

Attributes.Name: quadrant4
Attributes.Description: Q4 only

Attributes.Name: totalByPhase
Attributes.Description: In polyphase metering, the total by phase energy register is incremented when the sum of the absolute values of the phase energies is greater than zero: In single phase metering, the formulas for “Total” and “Total by phase” collapse to the same expression. For communication purposes however, the “Total” enumeration should be used with single phase meter data.

Entities.Name: PendingCalculation
Entities.Description: When present, a scalar conversion that needs to be applied to every IntervalReading.value contained in IntervalBlock. This conversion results in a new associated ReadingType, reflecting the true dimensions of IntervalReading values after the conversion.

Attributes.Name: multiplyBeforeAdd
Attributes.Description: Whether scalars should be applied before adding the 'offset'.

Attributes.Name: offset
Attributes.Description: (if applicable) Offset to be added as well as multiplication using scalars.

Attributes.Name: scalarDenominator
Attributes.Description: (if scalar is rational number) When 'IntervalReading.value' is multiplied by 'scalarNumerator' and divided by this value, it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur, resulting in the 'ReadingType.unit'.

Attributes.Name: scalarFloat
Attributes.Description: (if scalar is floating number) When multiplied with 'IntervalReading.value', it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur, according to the 'ReadingType.unit'.

Attributes.Name: scalarNumerator
Attributes.Description: (if scalar is integer or rational number)  When the scalar is a simple integer, and this attribute is presented alone and multiplied with 'IntervalReading.value', it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur, resulting in the 'ReadingType.unit'. It is never used in conjunction with 'scalarFloat', only with 'scalarDenominator'.

Entities.Name: EndDeviceAction
Entities.Description: Action/command performed by an end device on a device other than the end device.

DerivedEntities.Name: PanDemandResponse
DerivedEntities.Description: PAN control used to issue action/command to PAN devices during a demand response/load control event.

Attributes.Name: appliance
Attributes.Description: Appliance being controlled.

Attributes.Name: avgLoadAdjustment
Attributes.Description:
Used to define a maximum energy usage limit as a percentage of the client implementations specific average energy usage. The load adjustment percentage is added to 100% creating a percentage limit applied to the client implementations specific average energy usage. A -10% load adjustment percentage will establish an energy usage limit equal to 90% of the client implementations specific average energy usage. Each load adjustment percentage is referenced to the client implementations specific average energy usage. There are no cumulative effects.
The range of this field is -100% to +100% with a resolution of 1. A -100% value equals a total load shed. A +100% value will limit the energy usage to the client implementations specific average energy usage.

Attributes.Name: cancelControlMode
Attributes.Description: Encoding of cancel control.

Attributes.Name: cancelDateTime
Attributes.Description: Timestamp when a canceling of the event is scheduled to start.

Attributes.Name: cancelNow
Attributes.Description: If true, a canceling of the event should start immediately.

Attributes.Name: coolingOffset
Attributes.Description: Requested offset to apply to the normal cooling setpoint at the time of the start of the event. It represents a temperature change that will be applied to the associated cooling set point. The temperature offsets will be calculated per the local temperature in the thermostat. The calculated temperature will be interpreted as the number of degrees to be added to the cooling set point. Sequential demand response events are not cumulative. The offset shall be applied to the normal setpoint.

Attributes.Name: coolingSetpoint
Attributes.Description: Requested cooling set point. Temperature set point is typically defined and calculated based on local temperature.

Attributes.Name: criticalityLevel
Attributes.Description: Level of criticality for the action of this control. The action taken by load control devices for an event can be solely based on this value, or in combination with other load control event fields supported by the device.

Attributes.Name: dutyCycle
Attributes.Description: Maximum "on" state duty cycle as a percentage of time. For example, if the value is 80, the device would be in an "on" state for 80% of the time for the duration of the action.

Attributes.Name: enrollmentGroup
Attributes.Description: Provides a mechanism to direct load control actions to groups of PAN devices. It can be used in conjunction with the PAN device types.

Attributes.Name: heatingOffset
Attributes.Description: Requested offset to apply to the normal heating setpoint at the time of the start of the event. It represents a temperature change that will be applied to the associated heating set point. The temperature offsets will be calculated per the local temperature in the thermostat. The calculated temperature will be interpreted as the number of degrees to be subtracted from the heating set point. Sequential demand response events are not cumulative. The offset shall be applied to the normal setpoint.

Attributes.Name: heatingSetpoint
Attributes.Description: Requested heating set point. Temperature set point is typically defined and calculated based on local temperature.

Entities.Name: PriceDescriptor
Entities.Description: The price of a Commodity during a given time interval may change over time.  For example, a price may be forecasted a year ahead, a month ahead, a day ahead, an hour ahead, and in real time; this is defined using the MarketType. Additionally a price may have one or more components. For example, a locational marginal energy price may be the arithmetic sum of the system price, the congestion price, and the loss price.  The priceType enumeration is used determine if the price is the complete price (priceType="total") or one of potentially many constituent components.

Entities.Name: PositionPoint
Entities.Description: Set of spatial coordinates that determine a point, defined in the coordinate system specified in 'Location.CoordinateSystem'. Use a single position point instance to describe a point-oriented location. Use a sequence of position points to describe a line-oriented object (physical location of non-point oriented objects like cables or lines), or area of an object (like a substation or a geographical zone - in this case, have first and last position point with the same values).

Entities.Name: MarketLedger
Entities.Description: In accounting transactions, a ledger is a book containing accounts to which debits and credits are posted from journals, where transactions are initially recorded. Journal entries are periodically posted to the ledger. Ledger actual represents actual amounts by account within ledger within company or within business area. Actual amounts may be generated in a source application and then loaded to a specific ledger within the enterprise general ledger or budget application.
